(174, 1, 3, 'What is the half of the area of the triangle\nwhose vertices are (1:1), (3:1); (1:3) ?', '', 'top', '1', '2', '4', '5', 'A', 174, '<b>(A)&#10;</b>&#160;<div><div>Area of the triangle</div><div>$$=\\frac{1}{2} \\times\\left\\{x_{1}\\left(y_{2}-y_{3}\\right)+x_{2}\\left(y_{3}-y_{1}\\right)+x_{3}\\left(y_{1}-y_{2}\\right)\\right\\}$$<br></div></div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;<b>(OR)</b></div><div><b><img src=\"http://yellowandgray.com/exam-horse/img-exp/2019-174-Exp-01.png\">$$=\\frac{1}{2}[\\{(1 \\times 1)+(3 \\times 3)+(1 \\times 1)\\}-\\{(1 \\times 3)+(1 \\times 1)+(3 \\times 1)\\}]$$<br></b></div><div><b>$$=\\frac{1}{2} \\times\\{(1+9+1)-(3+1+3)\\}$$<br></b></div><div><b>$$=\\frac{1}{2} \\times\\{11-7\\}=\\frac{1}{2} \\times 4=2 \\mathrm{sq.units}$$<br></b></div><div><b>$\\frac{1}{2}$ of the area of the triangle $=\\frac{1}{2} \\times 2$ $=1$ sq.unit<br></b></div>', 'uploads/e6ae1c87750264cebcdc049319baa67d.jpg', 'top', '', 3, '14', '', '2020-03-17 12:56:52', '2020-03-12 12:20:16', 1, 1),
(175, 1, 3, 'A silver wire when bent in the form of a square&#10;encloses an area of 484 sqm; If the same wire&#10;is bent in the form of a circle, then find the diameter of the circle.&#160;$$\\left(\\text { use } \\pi=\\frac{22}{7}\\right)$$', '', 'top', '14m', '28m', '24m', '7m', 'B', 175, '<div><b>(B)</b></div>Area of the square = 484 <span>m</span><sup>2</sup><div>$$\\therefore \\text { Side of the square }=\\sqrt{484}=22 \\mathrm{m}$$<br></div><div>Perimeter of the square = 88 m&#160;</div><div>Perimeter of the square = Circumference of the circle = 88 m&#160;</div><div><span>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;2</span><span>&#8719;</span><span>r = 88 m</span><br></div><div><span><font face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span>$$r=88 \\times \\frac{1}{2} \\times \\frac{7}{22}$$</span></font><br></span></div><div><span><font face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; r = 14 m</span></font></span></div><div><span><font face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;Diameter = 2r</span><br></font></span></div><div><span><font face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;=&#160; 2 x 14 = 28m</span><br></font></span></div>', 'uploads/303fd5dc79f3be0d0ee1101d86663a66.jpg', 'top', '', 3, '14', '', '2020-03-17 10:27:02', '2020-03-12 12:20:16', 1, 1),
(176, 1, 3, 'In how much time will a sum of &#8377;1600 amount&#10;ro&#160;&#8377;1852.20 at 5%  per annum compound&#10;interest', '', 'top', '2 years', '3 years', '4 years', '5 years', 'B', 176, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(B)&#160;</b></font><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">Principal = Rs.1852.20 - 252.20 = Rs. 1600</font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$P\\left(1+\\frac{r}{100}\\right)^{n}=1852.20$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$1600\\left(1+\\frac{5}{100}\\right)^{n}=1852.20$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$1600 \\times\\left(\\frac{105}{100}\\right)^{n}=1852.20$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$\\left(\\frac{21}{20}\\right)^{n}=\\frac{1852.20}{1600}=\\frac{18522}{16000}$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$=\\frac{9261}{8000}$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$\\left(\\frac{21}{20}\\right)^{n}=\\frac{21^{3}}{20^{3}}=\\left(\\frac{21}{20}\\right)^{3}$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">,\'. n = 3</font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">No. of years = 3</font></div><div><div>&#10;&#10;</div></div>', '', '0', '', 3, '15', '', '2020-03-17 10:31:40', '2020-03-12 12:20:16', 1, 1),
