(363, 2, 3, 'Raju starts walking towards south. After&#10;walking 20 m he turns towards North and&#10;Walks 8m. Again he turns towards East&#10;and walks 5m. How far and in which&#10;direction is he from his starting point.', '', 'top', '15 m, South', '17 m, North-West', '7 m, East', '13 m, South-East', 'D', 161, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(D)</b></font><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">.\'. AC = AB - CB<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;= 20 - 8 = 12</font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$\\mathrm{AD}=\\sqrt{\\mathrm{AC}^{2}+\\mathrm{CD}^{2}}$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$=\\sqrt{12^{2}+5^{2}}=\\sqrt{144+25}=\\sqrt{169}$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">.\'.AD = 13m<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><div>From the starting point Raju is in South-East&#160;<span>Direction.</span></div></font></div>', 'uploads/94ec72b6af7495e55c74c05eda06f9ae.png', 'top', '', 3, '14', '', '2020-03-19 12:41:28', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
(364, 2, 3, 'The sides of 14 Square\'s are 11 cm, 12&#10;cm, 13 cm ________ 24 cm, then find the&#10;total area of 14 squares.', '', 'top', '3515 cm<sup>2</sup>', '4515 cm<sup>2</sup>', '2715 cm<sup>2</sup>', '3215 cm<sup>2</sup>', 'B', 162, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(B)</b></font><div><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Area of Square = side x side</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Total area of 14 squares = 11<sup>2</sup>+12<sup>2</sup>+13<sup>2</sup>+.....+24<sup>2</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">= (1<sup>2</sup> +2<sup>2</sup> + &#8230;.... +24<sup>2</sup>) - (1<sup>2</sup>+2<sup>2</sup>+.....&#10;+ 10<sup>2</sup>)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"> $$=\\left(\\frac{24(25)(49)}{6}\\right)-\\left(\\frac{10(11)(21)}{6}\\right)$$ </p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">= (4900 - 385) cm<sup>2</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">= 4515 cm<sup>2</sup></p></div>', '', '', '', 3, '14', '', '2020-03-19 12:46:42', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
(365, 2, 3, 'A Train travelled a certain distance at a&#10;uniform speed. If the train had been 7 km/hr&#10;faster, it would have. taken 14 hours less&#10;than the scheduled time. If the train were&#10;slower by 3km/hr then it would have taken&#10;10 hours more than the scheduled time.&#10;Find the distance covered by the train.', '', 'top', '600 km', '700 km', '800 km', '900 km', 'D', 163, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(D)</b></font><div><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Distance = D km</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">By given data,</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$\\frac{D}{x}-\\frac{D}{x+7}=14$$ &#8230;&#8230;&#8230;.(I)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$\\frac{D}{x-3}-\\frac{D}{x}=10$$ &#8230;&#8230;&#8230;..(II)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Where Speed = x km/h</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">From (l)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">=&gt;7D = 14 x (x+7)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">=&gt;D &#160;&#160;= 2 x (x+7)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">From (ll)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$=\\frac{[x-(x-3)]}{x(x-3)}=10$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">=&gt;3D = 10x(x-3)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$D=\\frac{10}{3} x(x-3)$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$\\therefore 2 x(x+7)=\\frac{10}{3} x(x-3)$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">=&gt;3x+21 = 5x- 15</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">2x = 36</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">x = 18 km/h</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Put this in (l)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$\\frac{D}{18}-\\frac{D}{25}=14 \\Rightarrow \\frac{25 D-18 D}{450}=14$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">=&gt;Distance D = 900 km</p></div>', '', '', '', 3, '14', '', '2020-03-19 12:13:52', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
(366, 2, 3, 'Find the average of first \'n\' natural\nnumbers', '', 'top', '$$\\frac{n(n+1)}{2}$$', '$$\\frac{n(n+1)(2 n+1)}{2}$$', '$$\\frac{n+1}{2}$$', '$$n^{2}$$', 'C', 164, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(C)</b></font><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">Sum of \'n\' natural numbers $=\\frac{n(n+1)}{2}$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">.\'. Average of first \'n\' natural numbers<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$=\\frac{n(n+1)}{2} \\div n$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$=\\frac{n+1}{2}$$<br></font></div>', '', '', '', 3, '14', '', '2020-03-17 05:03:16', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
(367, 2, 3, 'A gardener wanted to reward a girl for her\ngood deeds by giving some apples. He gave\n2 apples on the first day, 4 on the second day, 8 on the third day, 16 apples on the\nfourth day and so on for ten days. How\nmany apples did she get from the gardener\nat the end of the tenth day', '', 'top', '1024', '2060', '1760', '2046', 'D', 165, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(D)</b></font><div><p class=\"MsoNormal\">First day, apples donated = 2</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Second day, apples donated = 4 = 2<sup>2</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Third day, apples donated = 8 = 2<sup>3</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><sup>:</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><sup>:</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><sup>:</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">10th day, apples donated = 1024 = 2<sup>10</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">.\'. Total no. of apples got from gardener at the end of 10th day = 2+2<sup>2</sup>+2<sup>3</sup>+2<sup>4</sup>+&#8230;.+2<sup>10&#10;</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$S_{n}=\\frac{a\\left(r^{n}-1\\right)}{r-1} \\quad \\text { here } r=2 ;&#10;a=2$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$\\therefore&#10;\\mathrm{S}_{\\mathrm{n}}=\\frac{2\\left(2^{10}-1\\right)}{2-1}=2(1024-1)$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">= 2 x 1023 = 2046<sup></sup></p></div>', '', '', '', 3, '14', '', '2020-03-17 05:11:43', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
