(63, 1, 3, 'Due to increase of 30% in the price of a colour  TV the sale is reduced, by 40%. What will be percentage change in income ?', '', 'top', '10% increase', '10% decrease', '35% decrease', '22% decrease', 'D', 63, '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>Let the original sale be Rs.100&#160;</div><div>When it is reduced by 40% the sale will be 60%&#160;</div><div>Increase in the price = 30%&#160;</div><div>The income will be 100+30 = 130%</div><div>$\\therefore$ The income for $60 \\%$ of sale $=\\frac{60}{100} \\times 130=78 \\%$<br></div><div><span>.\'.&#160;</span>The income will be decreased by (100%-78%) = 22%</div>', '', '0', '', 3, '6', '', '2020-03-16 05:02:24', '2020-03-12 12:20:16', 1, 1),
(64, 1, 3, 'Find the least number which when divided by 24,32 and 36 leaves the remainders 19, 27 and 31 respectively.', '', 'top', '280', '290', '283', '300', 'C', 64, '<b>(C)</b>&#160;<div><br></div><div>L.C.M. = 4x3x2x4x3 = 288&#160;</div><div>24 - 19=5&#160;</div><div>32 - 27=5&#160;</div><div>36 - 31=5&#160;</div><div>Hence, \'5\' should be subtracted from 288&#10;since it leaves the remainders.</div><div>&#160;.\'. The least number is (288 - 5) = 283</div>', 'uploads/fe5c77d455234a51ad72b7151949aa32.png', 'top', '', 3, '6', '', '2020-03-16 04:41:19', '2020-03-12 12:20:16', 1, 1),
(65, 1, 3, 'If LCM of \"a\" and \"b\" is a and LCM of \"b\" and \"c\" is b. then what is the LCM of \"c\" and \"a\".', '', 'top', 'a', 'b', 'c', 'abc', 'A', 65, '<b>(A)</b><div>L.C.M of \'a\' and \'b\' = a&#160;<div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;a x b = a&#160;</div><div>$$b=\\frac{a}{a}=1$$&#160;</div><div>L.C.M of \'b\' and \'c\' = b</div><div>&#160;$$C=\\frac{b}{b}=1$$</div><div>.\'. L.C.M. of \'c&#8217; and \'a\'  =  1 x a = a</div></div>', '', '0', '', 3, '6', '', '2020-03-17 06:27:01', '2020-03-12 12:20:16', 1, 1),
(66, 1, 3, 'Which one is correct ?', '', 'top', '$$\\frac{-3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{1}{2}$$<br>', '$$-\\frac{3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{1}{2}$$<br>', '$$-\\frac{3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{1}{2}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{1}{2}&lt;\\frac{-3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}$$<br>', 'A', 66, '<div><b>(A)</b></div>$$\\text { A) } \\frac{-3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{1}{2}$$<br><div>$$=\\frac{-48&lt;-26-15&lt;-4&lt;40}{80}$$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{-48&lt;-26&lt;15&lt;-4&lt;40}{80}$$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{-48}{80}&lt;\\frac{-26}{80}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{-4}{80}&lt;\\frac{40}{80}$$<br></div><div>This is the correct order</div><div>&#160;Option (A) is correct.</div>', '', '0', '-', 3, '6', '', '2020-03-17 06:27:45', '2020-03-12 12:20:16', 1, 1),
(67, 1, 3, '$$\\text { Simplify } \\cdot \\frac{x^{2}-25}{x+3} \\div \\frac{(x+5)^{2}}{x^{2}-9}$$<br>', '', 'top', '$$\\frac{(x-5)(x+3)}{(x-3)}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{(x-5)(x-3)}{(x+5)}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{(x+5)(x-3)}{(x+3)}$$<br>', '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$\\frac{(x+5)(x+3)}{(x-5)}$$</font><br>', 'B', 67, '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp; \\frac{x^{2}-25}{x+3} \\div \\frac{(x+5)^{2}}{x^{2}-9} \\\\&#10;=&amp; \\frac{(x+5)(x-5)}{(x+3)} \\times \\frac{(x+3)(x-3)}{(x+5)(x+5)} \\\\&#10;=&amp; \\frac{(x-5)(x-3)}{(x+5)}&#10;\\end{aligned}$$</div>', '', '0', '', 3, '6', '', '2020-03-17 06:28:11', '2020-03-12 12:20:16', 1, 1),
(68, 1, 3, '$$\\text { Simplify } \\frac{2}{7}-\\left\\{\\left(\\frac{1}{4} \\div \\frac{2}{3}\\right)-\\frac{5}{6}\\right\\}$$<br>', '', 'top', '$$\\frac{168}{125}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{125}{160}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{125}{168}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{160}{125}$$<br>', 'C', 68, '<div><b>(C)</b></div>$$\\frac{2}{7}-\\left\\{\\left(\\frac{1}{4} \\div \\frac{2}{3}\\right)-\\frac{5}{6}\\right\\}$$<div>$$=\\frac{2}{7}-\\left\\{\\left(\\frac{1}{4} \\times \\frac{3}{2}\\right)-\\frac{5}{6}\\right\\}=\\frac{2}{7}-\\left\\{\\left(\\frac{3}{8}\\right)-\\frac{5}{6}\\right\\}$$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{2}{7}-\\left(\\frac{9-20}{24}\\right)=\\frac{2}{7}-\\left(\\frac{-11}{24}\\right)=\\frac{48+77}{168}=\\frac{125}{168}$$<br></div>', '', '0', '', 3, '6', '', '2020-03-17 06:28:42', '2020-03-12 12:20:16', 1, 1),
(69, 1, 3, 'The exterior angles of a pentagon are in the ratio 6:3:4:3:2. Find all its interior angles.', '', 'top', '60&#730;, 120&#730;, 80&#730;, 160&#730;, 120&#730;', '80&#730;, 110&#730;, 150&#730;, 120&#730;, 80&#730;', '100&#730;, 170&#730;, 160&#730;, 40&#730;, 70&#730;', '60&#730;, 120&#730;, 100&#730;, 120&#730;, 140&#730;', 'D', 69, '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>The sum of the exterior angles of a pentagon = 360<span>&#730;</span>&#160;</div><div>The ratio of the exterior angles of the pentagon is = 6:3:4:3:2:2&#160;</div><div>&#160;Let them be 6x,3x, 4x,3x, &amp; 2x&#160;</div><div>&#160;.\'. The exterior angles are&#160;</div><div><div>i) $\\frac{6 x}{18 x} \\times 360=120^{\\circ}$</div><div>ii) $\\frac{3 x}{18 x} \\times 360=60^{\\circ}$</div><div>iii) $\\frac{4 x}{18 x} \\times 360=80^{\\circ}$</div><div>iv) $\\frac{3 x}{18 x} \\times 360=60^{\\circ}$</div><div>v) $\\frac{2 x}{18 x} \\times 360=40^{\\circ}$</div></div><div><div>The exterior angles are 120<span>&#730;, 60</span><span>&#730;, 80</span><span>&#730;, 60</span><span>&#730;, 40</span><span>&#730;</span></div><div>.\'. The interior angles are</div><div>= ( 180<span>&#730;</span><span>-120</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), ( 180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-60</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), ( 180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-80</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), ( 180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-60</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), (180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-40</span><span>&#730;</span><span>)</span></div><div>= 60<span>&#730;, 120</span><span>&#730;, 100</span><span>&#730;, 120</span><span>&#730;, 140</span><span>&#730;</span></div></div>', 'uploads/f7fbcfabc30928201fbccc287d510d3c.jpg', 'top', '', 3, '6', '', '2020-03-16 04:49:12', '2020-03-12 12:20:16', 1, 1),
(70, 1, 3, 'Which one of the following cannot be the sides of a triangle ?', '', 'top', '4, 5, 6', '3, 4, 6', '2,<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"> </font>3, 4', '1,<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"> </font>2, 3', 'D', 70, '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>&#160;In a triangle, the sum of any two sides of it must be greater than the third side&#160;<div>&#160;A) 4, 5, 6 - triangle can be formed&#160;</div><div>&#160;B) 3, 4, 6 - triangle can be formed&#160;</div><div>&#160;C) 2,9,4 - triangle can be formed&#160;</div><div>&#160;D) 1,2,3 - 1+2=3;&#160;</div><div>&#160;Here the sum of the two sides is not&#160;<span>greater than the third side. A triangle</span></div><div>cannot be formed.</div><div>Hence the option (D) is the answer.<br></div></div>', '', '0', '', 3, '6', '', '2020-03-16 04:59:45', '2020-03-12 12:20:16', 1, 1),
