(174, 1, 3, 'What is the half of the area of the triangle\nwhose vertices are (1:1), (3:1); (1:3) ?', '', 'top', '1', '2', '4', '5', 'A', 174, '<b>(A)&#10;</b>&#160;<div><div>Area of the triangle</div><div>$$=\\frac{1}{2} \\times\\left\\{x_{1}\\left(y_{2}-y_{3}\\right)+x_{2}\\left(y_{3}-y_{1}\\right)+x_{3}\\left(y_{1}-y_{2}\\right)\\right\\}$$<br></div></div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;<b>(OR)</b></div><div><b><img src=\"http://yellowandgray.com/exam-horse/img-exp/2019-174-Exp-01.png\">$$=\\frac{1}{2}[\\{(1 \\times 1)+(3 \\times 3)+(1 \\times 1)\\}-\\{(1 \\times 3)+(1 \\times 1)+(3 \\times 1)\\}]$$<br></b></div><div><b>$$=\\frac{1}{2} \\times\\{(1+9+1)-(3+1+3)\\}$$<br></b></div><div><b>$$=\\frac{1}{2} \\times\\{11-7\\}=\\frac{1}{2} \\times 4=2 \\mathrm{sq.units}$$<br></b></div><div><b>$\\frac{1}{2}$ of the area of the triangle $=\\frac{1}{2} \\times 2$ $=1$ sq.unit<br></b></div>', 'uploads/e6ae1c87750264cebcdc049319baa67d.jpg', 'top', '', 3, '14', '', '2020-03-17 12:56:52', '2020-03-12 12:20:16', 1, 1),
