(363, 2, 3, 'Raiu starts walking towards south. After\nwalking 20 m he turns towards North and\nWalks 8m. Again he turns towards East\nand walks 5m. How far and in which\ndirection is he from his starting point.', '', 'top', '15 m, South', '17 m, North-West', '7 m, East', '13 m, South-East', 'D', 161, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(D)</b></font><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">.\'. AC = AB - CB<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;= 20 - 8 = 12</font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$\\mathrm{AD}=\\sqrt{\\mathrm{AC}^{2}+\\mathrm{CD}^{2}}$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$=\\sqrt{12^{2}+5^{2}}=\\sqrt{144+25}=\\sqrt{169}$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">.\'.AD = 13m<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><div>From the starting point Raju is in South-East&#160;<span>Direction.</span></div></font></div>', '', '', '', 3, '14', '', '2020-03-16 12:30:40', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
(364, 2, 3, 'The sides of 14 Square\'s are 1l cm, 12\ncrn, 13 cm ________ 24 cm, then find the\ntotal area of 14 squares.', '', 'top', '3515 cm2', '4515 cm2', '2715 cm2', '3215 cm2', 'B', 162, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(B)</b></font><div><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Area of Square = side x side</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Total area of 14 squares = 11<sup>2</sup>+12<sup>2</sup>+13<sup>2</sup>+.....+24<sup>2</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">= (1<sup>2</sup> +2<sup>2</sup> + &#8230;.... +24<sup>2</sup>) - (1<sup>2</sup>+2<sup>2</sup>+.....&#10;+ 10<sup>2</sup>)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$=\\left(\\frac{24(25)(49)}{6}\\right)-\\left(\\frac{10(11)(21)}{6}\\right)$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">= (4900 - 385) cm<sup>2</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">= 4515 cm<sup>2</sup></p></div>', '', '', '', 3, '14', '', '2020-03-16 12:35:11', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
(365, 2, 3, 'A Train travelled a certain distance at a\nuniform speed. If the. train had been 7 km/hr\nfaster, it would have. taken 14 hours less\nthan the scheduled time. If the train were\nslower by 3limihr then it would have tiken\n10 hours more than the scheduled time.\nFind the distance covered by the train.', '', 'top', '600 km', '700 km', '800 km', '900 km', 'D', 163, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(D)</b></font><div><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Distance = D km</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">By given data,</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$\\frac{D}{x}-\\frac{D}{x+7}=14$$ &#8230;&#8230;&#8230;.(I)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$\\frac{D}{x-3}-\\frac{D}{x}=10$$ &#8230;&#8230;&#8230;..(II)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Where Speed = x km/h</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">From (l)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">=&gt;7D = 14 x (x+7)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">=&gt;D &#160;&#160;= 2 x (x+7)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">From (ll)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$=\\frac{[x-(x-3)]}{x(x-3)}=10$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">=&gt;3D = 10x(x-3)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$D=\\frac{10}{3} x(x-3)$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$\\therefore 2 x(x+7)=\\frac{10}{3} x(x-3)$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">=&gt;3x+21 = 5x- 15</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">2x = 36</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">x = 18 km/h</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Put this in (l)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$\\frac{D}{18}-\\frac{D}{25}=14 \\Rightarrow \\frac{25 D-18 D}{450}=14$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">=&gt;Distance D = 900 km</p></div>', '', '', '', 3, '14', '', '2020-03-17 05:01:35', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
