(367, 2, 3, 'A gardener wanted to reward a girl for her\ngood deeds by giving some apples. He gave\n2 apples on the first day, 4 on the second day, 8 on the third day, 16 apples on the\nfourth day and so on for ten days. How\nmany apples did she get from the gardener\nat the end of the tenth day', '', 'top', '1024', '2060', '1760', '2046', 'D', 165, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(D)</b></font><div><p class=\"MsoNormal\">First day, apples donated = 2</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Second day, apples donated = 4 = 2<sup>2</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Third day, apples donated = 8 = 2<sup>3</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><sup>:</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><sup>:</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><sup>:</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">10th day, apples donated = 1024 = 2<sup>10</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">.\'. Total no. of apples got from gardener at the end of 10th day = 2+2<sup>2</sup>+2<sup>3</sup>+2<sup>4</sup>+&#8230;.+2<sup>10&#10;</sup></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$S_{n}=\\frac{a\\left(r^{n}-1\\right)}{r-1} \\quad \\text { here } r=2 ;&#10;a=2$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$\\therefore&#10;\\mathrm{S}_{\\mathrm{n}}=\\frac{2\\left(2^{10}-1\\right)}{2-1}=2(1024-1)$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">= 2 x 1023 = 2046<sup></sup></p></div>', '', '', '', 3, '14', '', '2020-03-17 05:11:43', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
