Normal\">required ratio (cone, hemisphere, cylinder) (i.e) 1 : 2 : 3</p></div>', '', '', '', 3, '15', '', '2020-03-17 05:21:36', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
(369, 2, 3, 'Spherical metal ball of radius 6 cm is&#10;melted and casted into small spherical&#10;balls having diameter 6 mm. How many&#10;small balls can be casted', '', 'top', '8000', '1000', '6000', '2000', 'A', 167, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(A)</b></font><div><p class=\"MsoNormal\">radius of big metal ball = 60mm</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">radius of small metal ball = 3mm</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$\\text { Total no. of small balls }=\\frac{\\frac{4}{3} \\pi&#10;R^{3}}{\\frac{4}{3} \\pi r^{3}}$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Here R = 60mm, r= 3mm</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$=\\frac{60 \\times 60 \\times 60}{3 \\times 3 \\times 3}$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">= 20 x 20 x 20</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">= 8000 balls</p></div>', '', '', '', 3, '15', '', '2020-03-17 05:25:32', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
