(371, 2, 3, 'The present age of A and B are in the ratio\n4:5 and after five years they will be in the ratio 5:6 then their sum of present age is', '', 'top', '55 years', '45 years', '35 years', '25 years', 'B', 169, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span>(B)</span></b><span></span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Ratio of present ages of A and B is&#10;4:5</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>After 5 years their age ratio is 5:6</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>$$\\text { (i.e) }&#10;\\frac{x}{y}=\\frac{4}{5}$$ &#8230;&#8230;.. (I)</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>$$\\frac{x+5}{y+5}=\\frac{5}{6}$$ &#8230;&#8230;&#8230;&#10;(II)</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>(l) gives 5x = 4y &#8230;&#8230;..(III)</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>(ll) gives 6x + 30 = 5y + 25</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>(i.e) 6x - 5Y = -5 &#8230;.....(IV)</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>From (lll) and (lV)</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>30x - 24y = 0</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>30x - 25y = -25</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;........&#160; &#160; &#160;&#10;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;&#10;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;&#10;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;&#10;&#160; &#160; &#160;y = 25</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>$$\\therefore x=\\frac{4}{5} \\times&#10;25=20$$</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>.\'. Sum of their present age = 20 +&#10;25 = 45 yrs</span></p>', '', '', '', 3, '15', '', '2020-03-17 05:39:29', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
(372, 2, 3, 'lt A and B can do a work in 6 dfys, B and\nC can do it in 12 days, C and A can do it\nin 4 days how many days it would take to\nfinish the same work by all the three\ntogether ?', '', 'top', '8 days', '4 days', '10 days', '2 days', 'B', 170, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">(B)</font><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$(A+B)^{\\prime} \\</font><span>text&#160;</span><span>{ \'s } 1 \\text { day\'s work }=\\frac{1}{6}$$</span></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$(\\mathrm{B}+\\mathrm{C})^{\\prime} \\text { \'s } 1 \\text { day\'s work }=\\frac{1}{12}$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$(C+A)^{\\prime} s 1 \\text { day\'s work }=\\frac{1}{4}$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$\\therefore 2\\left(\\frac{1}{A}+\\frac{1}{B}+\\frac{1}{C}\\right)=\\frac{1}{6}+\\frac{1}{12}+\\frac{1}{4}=\\frac{2+1+3}{12}=\\frac{6}{12}=\\frac{1}{2}$$<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">.\'. A, B and C together can finish the same work&#160;</font><span><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">in 2 x 2 days (i.e) 4 days.</font></span><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><br></font></div>', '', '', '', 3, '15', '', '2020-03-17 05:43:36', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
(373, 2, 3, 'A and B can complete a work individually\nin 12 days and 18 days. They started doing\nthe work together. But after 4 days A had\nto leave and B alone completed the\nremaining work. The whole work was\ncompleted in', '', 'top', '30 days', '20 days', '12 days', '8 days', 'C', 171, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(C)</b></font><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$(\\mathrm{A}+\\mathrm{B})^{\\prime} \\mathrm{s} \\text { 4 days work }=4\\left(\\frac{1}{12}+\\frac{1}{18}\\right)$$</font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$=4\\left(\\frac{3+2}{36}\\right)=\\frac{5}{9}$$<br></font><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$\\therefore$ Remaining work $=1-\\frac{5}{9}=\\frac{4}{9}$<br></font></div></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">B alone can do the full work in 18 days.<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">B can do $\\frac{4}{9}$ work in $\\frac{4}{9} \\times 18$ (ie) 8 days<br></font></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><div>Whole work was completed in (4+8) days</div><div>(i.e) 12 days.</div></font></div>', '', '', '', 3, '15', '', '2020-03-17 05:47:09', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
(374, 2, 3, 'A function $f:\\{-7,6) \\Rightarrow R$ is defined as $$\\begin{aligned}\n&\\text { follows } f(x)=\\left\\{\\begin{array}{cl}\nx^{2}+2 x+1 & -7 \\leq x<-5 \\\\\nx+5 & -5 \\leq x \\leq 2 \\\\\nx-1 & 2<x<6\n\\end{array}\\text { what }\\right.\\\\\n&\\text { is the value of } \\frac{4 f(-3)-2 f(4)}{f(-6)-4 f(1)} ?\n\\end{aligned}$$', '', 'top', '$$\\frac{2}{7}$$', '$$\\frac{7}{2}$$', '2', '$$\\frac{1}{2}$$', 'C', 172, '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(C)</b></font><div><p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#402;(-3)&#10;= x+5 = -3+5 = 2</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#402;(4)&#10;&#160;= x-1&#160; = 4&#8211;1 &#160;= 3</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#402;(-6)&#10;= x<sup>2</sup> +&#10;2 x&#10;+1 = 36 &#8211; 12 + 1 = 25</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#402;(1)&#10;= x + 5 = 1 + 5 = 6</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$\\frac{4&#10;f(-3)-2 f(4)}{f(-6)-4 f(1)}=\\left(\\frac{(4 \\times 2)-(2 \\times 3)}{25-(4 \\times&#10;6)}\\right)$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$=\\frac{8-6}{25-24}=\\frac{2}{1}=2$$</p></div>', '', '', '', 3, '15', '', '2020-03-17 05:56:44', '2020-03-16 09:11:16', 1, 1),
