(194, 31, 64, 'Find the least number which when divided by 24,32 and 36 leaves the remainders 19, 27 and 31 respectively.', '', 'top', '280', '290', '283', '300', 'C', 64, 'B', '(C)&#10;&#10;$$\\begin{array}{l}&#10;4[24,32,36 \\\\&#10;3 \\underline{6,8,9} \\\\&#10;\\frac{2 | 2,8,3}{1,4,3}&#10;\\end{array}$$&#10;L.C.M. = 4x3x2x4x3 = 288&#10;24 - 19=5&#10;32 - 27=5&#10;36 - 31=5&#10;Hence, \'5\' should be subtracted from 288&#10;since it leaves the remainders.&#10;.\'. The least number is (288 - 5) = 283', '', '0', '2020-03-14 00:00:00', '2020-03-14 00:00:00', 1),
