(416, 60, 56, 'A person crosses 600 m long street in 5 minutes. What is his speed in km Per hour?&#160;', '', 'top', '3.6', '7.2', '8.4', '10', 'B', 56, 'A', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\text { The person\'s speed }=\\frac{600 \\mathrm{m} \\times 60 \\mathrm{min}}{5 \\mathrm{min} \\times 1000 \\mathrm{m}} \\mathrm{km}\\\\&#10;&amp;=\\frac{36000}{5000}=7.2 \\mathrm{km}&#10;\\end{aligned}$$</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(417, 60, 57, 'A man travelled 2/11 of his journey by coach,17/22 by rail and walked the remaining 1 km. How far did he go ?', '', 'top', '22 km', '20 km', '33 km', '27 km', 'A', 57, 'D', '<b>(A)</b>&#160;<div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">Let the distance covered by him be x km.</font></div><div><div>$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\therefore x-\\left(\\frac{2}{11} x+\\frac{17}{22} x\\right)=1 \\mathrm{km}\\\\&#10;&amp;x-\\left(\\frac{4 x+17 x}{22}\\right)=1 \\mathrm{km}\\\\&#10;&amp;x-\\frac{21}{22} x=1 \\mathrm{km}&#10;\\end{aligned}$$&#10;$$\\frac{22 x-21 x}{22}=1 \\mathrm{km}$$&#10;$$x=1 \\times 22=22 \\mathrm{km}$$&#10;&#8756; The distance he went = 22Km</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(418, 60, 58, 'A ramp for unloading a moving truck has an angle of elevation of 30<span>&#730;</span>. If the top of the ramp is 0.9 m above the ground level then find the length of the ramp.', '', 'top', '2 m', '1.5 m', '1.8 m', '1.6 m', 'C', 58, 'D', '<b>(C)&#160;</b><div>&#160;In the figure, Ac is the ramp.&#10;Let the length of the ramp be \'l \' m&#10;$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\sin 30=\\frac{0.9}{1}\\\\&#10;&amp;\\frac{1}{2}=\\frac{0.9}{1}&#10;\\end{aligned}$$&#10;l=0.9 x 2m = 1.8m&#10;.\'. The length of the ramp = 1.8 m</div>', 'uploads/da593f1e3fb9c019d2d43fa18a64a9e8.jpg', 'top', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(419, 60, 59, 'The standard deviation of 10 values is 3. If each value is increased by 4 find the variance of the new set of value.', '', 'top', '30', '12', '9', '$$\\sqrt{3}$$', 'C', 59, 'B', '(c)&#10;&#10;If each value of a set is increased by some number evenly, &#10;there will be no increase in the standard deviation and the variance.&#160;<div>&#10;Hence the standard deviation of the 10 values will be the same.&#160;<div>&#10;Therefore, &#10;The variance of the new set of value = &#160;$$3^{2}=9$$</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(420, 60, 60, 'Find the next term of this sequence 11, 13, 17, 19, 23, .....', '', 'top', '25', '27', '29', '31', 'C', 60, 'B', '(c)&#10;&#10;11, 13, 77, 19,23, .......&#10;In this sequence all the terms are 2-digit prime numbers starting from 11.&#160;<div>Hence the next prime number in this sequence will be \'29\'.</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(421, 60, 61, 'Find the mean of 2,4,6, 8, 10, 12, 14, 16', '', 'top', '10', '9', '12', '14', 'B', 61, 'C', '(B)&#10;&#10;2, 4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 14, 16&#10;Here are 8 values totally.&#10;$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;\\therefore \\text { Mean } &amp;=\\frac{2+4+6+8+10+12+14+16}{8} \\\\&#10;&amp;=\\frac{72}{8}=9&#10;\\end{aligned}$$', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(422, 60, 62, 'Shyam\'s monthly income is Rs.12,000. He saves Rs.1200. Find the percent of his savings and his expenditure', '', 'top', '10%,80%', '10%, 90%', '80%, 10%', '90%\' 10%', 'B', 62, 'D', '<table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"324\">&#10; <tbody><tr>&#10;  <td width=\"210\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br></p></td><td width=\"114\" colspan=\"2\"></td></tr><tr><td width=\"210\" valign=\"top\"><table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"324\">&#10; <tbody><tr>&#10;  <td width=\"210\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>(B)</b></p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"114\" colspan=\"2\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;</p></td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"210\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">Shyam\'s monthly income</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"24\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">=</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"90\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">Rs. 12,000</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"210\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">Savings</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"24\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">=</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"90\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">Rs.&#160; &#160;&#160;1200</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"210\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Expenditure</p>&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;&#160;&#160; &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"24\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;</p>&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">=</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"90\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">--------------<br>&#10;  Rs. 10,800<br>&#10;  --------------</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10;</tbody></table></td><td width=\"24\" valign=\"top\"></td><td width=\"90\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10;</tbody></table><span>$\\%$ of his savings $=\\frac{1200}{12000} \\times 100=10 \\%$&#160;</span><div><span>$\\%$ of his expenditure $=\\frac{10800}{12000} \\times 100=90 \\%$&#160;</span></div><div>$\\therefore$ The percentages of savings &amp; expenditure&#10;$=10 \\%, 90 \\%$</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(423, 60, 63, 'Due to increase of 30% in the price of a colour  TV the sale is reduced, by 40%. What will be percentage change in income ?', '', 'top', '10% increase', '10% decrease', '35% decrease', '22% decrease', 'D', 63, 'D', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>Let the original sale be Rs.100&#160;</div><div>When it is reduced by 40% the sale will be 60%&#160;</div><div>Increase in the price = 30%&#160;</div><div>The income will be 100+30 = 130%</div><div>$\\therefore$ The income for $60 \\%$ of sale $=\\frac{60}{100} \\times 130=78 \\%$<br></div><div><span>.\'.&#160;</span>The income will be decreased by (100%-78%) = 22%</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(424, 60, 64, 'Find the least number which when divided by 24,32 and 36 leaves the remainders 19, 27 and 31 respectively.', '', 'top', '280', '290', '283', '300', 'C', 64, 'D', '<b>(C)</b>&#160;<div><br></div><div>L.C.M. = 4x3x2x4x3 = 288&#160;</div><div>24 - 19=5&#160;</div><div>32 - 27=5&#160;</div><div>36 - 31=5&#160;</div><div>Hence, \'5\' should be subtracted from 288&#10;since it leaves the remainders.</div><div>&#160;.\'. The least number is (288 - 5) = 283</div>', 'uploads/fe5c77d455234a51ad72b7151949aa32.png', 'top', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(425, 60, 65, 'If LCM of \"a\" and \"b\" is a and LCM of \"b\" and \"c\" is b. then what is the LCM of \"c\" and \"a\".', '', 'top', 'a', 'b', 'c', 'abc', 'A', 65, 'D', '(A)&#10;&#10;L.C.M of \'a\' and \'b\' = a&#160;<div>a x b = a&#160;</div><div>$$b=\\frac{a}{a}=1$$&#160;</div><div>L.C.M of \'b\' and \'c\' = b</div><div>&#160;$$C=\\frac{b}{b}=1$$</div><div>.\'. L.C.M. of \'c&#8217; and \'a\'  =  1 x a = a</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1);
