(441, 61, 63, 'Due to increase of 30% in the price of a colour  TV the sale is reduced, by 40%. What will be percentage change in income ?', '', 'top', '10% increase', '10% decrease', '35% decrease', '22% decrease', 'D', 63, 'D', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>Let the original sale be Rs.100&#160;</div><div>When it is reduced by 40% the sale will be 60%&#160;</div><div>Increase in the price = 30%&#160;</div><div>The income will be 100+30 = 130%</div><div>$\\therefore$ The income for $60 \\%$ of sale $=\\frac{60}{100} \\times 130=78 \\%$<br></div><div><span>.\'.&#160;</span>The income will be decreased by (100%-78%) = 22%</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(442, 61, 64, 'Find the least number which when divided by 24,32 and 36 leaves the remainders 19, 27 and 31 respectively.', '', 'top', '280', '290', '283', '300', 'C', 64, 'C', '<b>(C)</b>&#160;<div><br></div><div>L.C.M. = 4x3x2x4x3 = 288&#160;</div><div>24 - 19=5&#160;</div><div>32 - 27=5&#160;</div><div>36 - 31=5&#160;</div><div>Hence, \'5\' should be subtracted from 288&#10;since it leaves the remainders.</div><div>&#160;.\'. The least number is (288 - 5) = 283</div>', 'uploads/fe5c77d455234a51ad72b7151949aa32.png', 'top', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
