(471, 64, 56, 'A person crosses 600 m long street in 5 minutes. What is his speed in km Per hour?&#160;', '', 'top', '3.6', '7.2', '8.4', '10', 'B', 56, 'C', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\text { The person\'s speed }=\\frac{600 \\mathrm{m} \\times 60 \\mathrm{min}}{5 \\mathrm{min} \\times 1000 \\mathrm{m}} \\mathrm{km}\\\\&#10;&amp;=\\frac{36000}{5000}=7.2 \\mathrm{km}&#10;\\end{aligned}$$</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(472, 64, 57, 'A man travelled 2/11 of his journey by coach,17/22 by rail and walked the remaining 1 km. How far did he go ?', '', 'top', '22 km', '20 km', '33 km', '27 km', 'A', 57, 'C', '<b>(A)</b>&#160;<div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">Let the distance covered by him be x km.</font></div><div><div>$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\therefore x-\\left(\\frac{2}{11} x+\\frac{17}{22} x\\right)=1 \\mathrm{km}\\\\&#10;&amp;x-\\left(\\frac{4 x+17 x}{22}\\right)=1 \\mathrm{km}\\\\&#10;&amp;x-\\frac{21}{22} x=1 \\mathrm{km}&#10;\\end{aligned}$$&#10;$$\\frac{22 x-21 x}{22}=1 \\mathrm{km}$$&#10;$$x=1 \\times 22=22 \\mathrm{km}$$&#10;&#8756; The distance he went = 22Km</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(473, 64, 59, 'The standard deviation of 10 values is 3. If each value is increased by 4 find the variance of the new set of value.', '', 'top', '30', '12', '9', '$$\\sqrt{3}$$', 'C', 59, 'C', '(c)&#10;&#10;If each value of a set is increased by some number evenly, &#10;there will be no increase in the standard deviation and the variance.&#160;<div>&#10;Hence the standard deviation of the 10 values will be the same.&#160;<div>&#10;Therefore, &#10;The variance of the new set of value = &#160;$$3^{2}=9$$</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
