(516, 66, 66, 'Which one is correct ?', '', 'top', '$$\\frac{-3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{1}{2}$$<br>', '$$-\\frac{3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{1}{2}$$<br>', '$$-\\frac{3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{1}{2}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{1}{2}&lt;\\frac{-3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}$$<br>', 'A', 66, 'B', '$$\\text { A) } \\frac{-3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{1}{2}$$<br><div>$$=\\frac{-48&lt;-26-15&lt;-4&lt;40}{80}$$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{-48&lt;-26&lt;15&lt;-4&lt;40}{80}$$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{-48}{80}&lt;\\frac{-26}{80}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{-4}{80}&lt;\\frac{40}{80}$$<br></div><div>This is the correct order</div><div>&#160;Option (A) is correct.</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(517, 66, 67, '$$\\text { Simplify } \\cdot \\frac{x^{2}-25}{x+3} \\div \\frac{(x+5)^{2}}{x^{2}-9}$$<br>', '', 'top', '$$\\frac{(x-5)(x+3)}{(x-3)}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{(x-5)(x-3)}{(x+5)}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{(x+5)(x-3)}{(x+3)}$$<br>', '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$\\frac{(x+5)(x+3)}{(x-5)}$$</font><br>', 'B', 67, 'A', '(B)\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\frac{x^{2}-25}{x+3} \\div \\frac{(x+5)^{2}}{x^{2}-9} \\\\\n=& \\frac{(x+5)(x-5)}{(x+3)} \\times \\frac{(x+3)(x-3)}{(x+5)(x+5)} \\\\\n=& \\frac{(x-5)(x-3)}{(x+5)}\n\\end{aligned}$$', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(518, 66, 68, '$$\\text { Simplify } \\frac{2}{7}-\\left\\{\\left(\\frac{1}{4} \\div \\frac{2}{3}\\right)-\\frac{5}{6}\\right\\}$$<br>', '', 'top', '$$\\frac{168}{125}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{125}{160}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{125}{168}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{160}{125}$$<br>', 'C', 68, 'A', '$$\\frac{2}{7}-\\left\\{\\left(\\frac{1}{4} \\div \\frac{2}{3}\\right)-\\frac{5}{6}\\right\\}$$<div>$$=\\frac{2}{7}-\\left\\{\\left(\\frac{1}{4} \\times \\frac{3}{2}\\right)-\\frac{5}{6}\\right\\}=\\frac{2}{7}-\\left\\{\\left(\\frac{3}{8}\\right)-\\frac{5}{6}\\right\\}$$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{2}{7}-\\left(\\frac{9-20}{24}\\right)=\\frac{2}{7}-\\left(\\frac{-11}{24}\\right)=\\frac{48+77}{168}=\\frac{125}{168}$$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(519, 66, 69, 'The exterior angles of a pentagon are in the ratio 6:3:4:3:2. Find all its interior angles.', '', 'top', '60&#730;, 120&#730;, 80&#730;, 160&#730;, 120&#730;', '80&#730;, 110&#730;, 150&#730;, 120&#730;, 80&#730;', '100&#730;, 170&#730;, 160&#730;, 40&#730;, 70&#730;', '60&#730;, 120&#730;, 100&#730;, 120&#730;, 140&#730;', 'D', 69, 'B', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>The sum of the exterior angles of a pentagon = 360<span>&#730;</span>&#160;</div><div>The ratio of the exterior angles of the pentagon is = 6:3:4:3:2:2&#160;</div><div>&#160;Let them be 6x,3x, 4x,3x, &amp; 2x&#160;</div><div>&#160;.\'. The exterior angles are&#160;</div><div><div>i) $\\frac{6 x}{18 x} \\times 360=120^{\\circ}$</div><div>ii) $\\frac{3 x}{18 x} \\times 360=60^{\\circ}$</div><div>iii) $\\frac{4 x}{18 x} \\times 360=80^{\\circ}$</div><div>iv) $\\frac{3 x}{18 x} \\times 360=60^{\\circ}$</div><div>v) $\\frac{2 x}{18 x} \\times 360=40^{\\circ}$</div></div><div><div>The exterior angles are 120<span>&#730;, 60</span><span>&#730;, 80</span><span>&#730;, 60</span><span>&#730;, 40</span><span>&#730;</span></div><div>.\'. The interior angles are</div><div>= ( 180<span>&#730;</span><span>-120</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), ( 180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-60</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), ( 180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-80</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), ( 180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-60</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), (180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-40</span><span>&#730;</span><span>)</span></div><div>= 60<span>&#730;, 120</span><span>&#730;, 100</span><span>&#730;, 120</span><span>&#730;, 140</span><span>&#730;</span></div></div>', 'uploads/f7fbcfabc30928201fbccc287d510d3c.jpg', 'top', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(520, 66, 70, 'Which one of the following cannot be the sides of a triangle ?', '', 'top', '4, 5, 6', '3, 4, 6', '2,<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"> </font>3, 4', '1,<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"> </font>2, 3', 'D', 70, 'B', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>&#160;In a triangle, the sum of any two sides of it must be greater than the third side&#160;<div>&#160;A) 4, 5, 6 - triangle can be formed&#160;</div><div>&#160;B) 3, 4, 6 - triangle can be formed&#160;</div><div>&#160;C) 2,9,4 - triangle can be formed&#160;</div><div>&#160;D) 1,2,3 - 1+2=3;&#160;</div><div>&#160;Here the sum of the two sides is not&#160;<span>greater than the third side. A triangle</span></div><div>cannot be formed.</div><div>Hence the option (D) is the answer.<br></div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(521, 66, 71, 'Without using logarithm table find approximate value for <span>log</span><sub>10</sub><span> 2.</span><br>', '', 'top', '0.2401', '0.3', '0.3802', '1.414', 'B', 71, 'B', '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(B)</b></font><div><table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">&#10; <tbody><tr>&#10;  <td width=\"470\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>$$2^{10}=1024$$</span></p>&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>$$2^{10} \\sim 1000$$</span></p>&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>$$10 \\log _{10} 2 \\sim 3$$</span></p>&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>$$\\log _{10} 2 \\quad \\sim \\frac{3}{10}$$</span></p>&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>$$\\log _{10} 2 \\quad \\sim \\quad 0.3 \\text {&#10;  (approximately) }$$</span></p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"168\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160;</span></p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10;</tbody></table></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1);
