(530, 67, 58, 'A ramp for unloading a moving truck has an angle of elevation of 30<span>&#730;</span>. If the top of the ramp is 0.9 m above the ground level then find the length of the ramp.', '', 'top', '2 m', '1.5 m', '1.8 m', '1.6 m', 'C', 58, 'A', '<b>(C)&#160;</b><div>&#160;In the figure, Ac is the ramp.&#10;Let the length of the ramp be \'l \' m&#10;$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\sin 30=\\frac{0.9}{1}\\\\&#10;&amp;\\frac{1}{2}=\\frac{0.9}{1}&#10;\\end{aligned}$$&#10;l=0.9 x 2m = 1.8m&#10;.\'. The length of the ramp = 1.8 m</div>', 'uploads/da593f1e3fb9c019d2d43fa18a64a9e8.jpg', 'top', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(531, 67, 59, 'The standard deviation of 10 values is 3. If each value is increased by 4 find the variance of the new set of value.', '', 'top', '30', '12', '9', '$$\\sqrt{3}$$', 'C', 59, 'B', '(c)&#10;&#10;If each value of a set is increased by some number evenly, &#10;there will be no increase in the standard deviation and the variance.&#160;<div>&#10;Hence the standard deviation of the 10 values will be the same.&#160;<div>&#10;Therefore, &#10;The variance of the new set of value = &#160;$$3^{2}=9$$</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(532, 67, 63, 'Due to increase of 30% in the price of a colour  TV the sale is reduced, by 40%. What will be percentage change in income ?', '', 'top', '10% increase', '10% decrease', '35% decrease', '22% decrease', 'D', 63, 'B', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>Let the original sale be Rs.100&#160;</div><div>When it is reduced by 40% the sale will be 60%&#160;</div><div>Increase in the price = 30%&#160;</div><div>The income will be 100+30 = 130%</div><div>$\\therefore$ The income for $60 \\%$ of sale $=\\frac{60}{100} \\times 130=78 \\%$<br></div><div><span>.\'.&#160;</span>The income will be decreased by (100%-78%) = 22%</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
