(584, 70, 54, 'In a right triangular ground, the sides adjacent to the right angle are 50 m and 80 m. Find the cost of cementing the ground at Rs.5/sq.m', '', 'top', '&#8377;20000', '&#8377;15000', '&#8377;10000', '&#8377;12500', 'C', 54, 'B', '(C)&#10;&#10;&#34;In the right triangular ground ABC, AB becomes the height of the triangle &#10;And BC becomes the base of the triangle.&#10;Area of the triangle$$=\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\mathrm{AB} \\times \\mathrm{BC}=\\frac{1}{2} \\times 80 \\times 50=2000 \\mathrm{sq.m}$$&#10;.\'. The cost of cementing ground @ Rs.5/sq.m. &#10;&#10;    2000x5=Rs.10,000/-&#10;', 'uploads/3c206566a40113c85e440734cd5b9f7e.jpg', 'top', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
