(709, 102, 257, '$$\\text { Simplify }: \\frac{x+3}{x^{3}-1} \\div \\frac{3 x+9}{x^{2}+x+1}$$', '', 'top', '$$\\frac{1}{3 x+1}$$', '3x + 1', '$$\\frac{1}{3 x-1}$$', '3x - 1', 'D', 56, 'B', '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><b>(D)</b></font><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"><div>$\\left(x^{3}-1\\right)=(x-1)\\left(x^{2}+x+1\\right)$</div><div>$\\left(x^{2}+x+1\\right)=\\frac{\\left(x^{3}-1\\right)}{(x-1)}$</div><div>Given expression may be written as</div><div>$\\frac{(x+3)}{\\left(x^{3}-1\\right)} \\div \\frac{3(x+3)(x-1)}{\\left(x^{3}-1\\right)}$</div><div>(i.e) $\\frac{(x+3)}{(x-1)\\left(x^{2}+x+1\\right)} \\div \\frac{3(x+3)(x-1)}{(x-1)\\left(x^{2}+x+1\\right)}$</div><div>(i.e) $\\quad \\frac{(x+3)}{3(x+3)(x-1)}=\\frac{1}{3 x-3}$</div></font></div>', '', '', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
