(753, 105, 58, 'A ramp for unloading a moving truck has an angle of elevation of 30<span>&#730;</span>. If the top of the ramp is 0.9 m above the ground level then find the length of the ramp.', '', 'top', '2 m', '1.5 m', '1.8 m', '1.6 m', 'C', 58, 'A', '<b>(C)&#160;</b><div>&#160;In the figure, Ac is the ramp.&#10;Let the length of the ramp be \'l \' m&#10;$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\sin 30=\\frac{0.9}{1}\\\\&#10;&amp;\\frac{1}{2}=\\frac{0.9}{1}&#10;\\end{aligned}$$&#10;l=0.9 x 2m = 1.8m&#10;.\'. The length of the ramp = 1.8 m</div>', 'uploads/da593f1e3fb9c019d2d43fa18a64a9e8.jpg', 'top', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(754, 105, 59, 'The standard deviation of 10 values is 3. If each value is increased by 4 find the variance of the new set of value.', '', 'top', '30', '12', '9', '$$\\sqrt{3}$$', 'C', 59, 'C', '(c)&#10;&#10;If each value of a set is increased by some number evenly, &#10;there will be no increase in the standard deviation and the variance.&#160;<div>&#10;Hence the standard deviation of the 10 values will be the same.&#160;<div>&#10;Therefore, &#10;The variance of the new set of value = &#160;$$3^{2}=9$$</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(755, 105, 60, 'Find the next term of this sequence 11, 13, 17, 19, 23, .....', '', 'top', '25', '27', '29', '31', 'C', 60, 'B', '(c)&#10;&#10;11, 13, 77, 19,23, .......&#10;In this sequence all the terms are 2-digit prime numbers starting from 11.&#160;<div>Hence the next prime number in this sequence will be \'29\'.</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
(756, 105, 61, 'Find the mean of 2,4,6, 8, 10, 12, 14, 16', '', 'top', '10', '9', '12', '14', 'B', 61, 'A', '(B)&#10;&#10;2, 4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 14, 16&#10;Here are 8 values totally.&#10;$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;\\therefore \\text { Mean } &amp;=\\frac{2+4+6+8+10+12+14+16}{8} \\\\&#10;&amp;=\\frac{72}{8}=9&#10;\\end{aligned}$$', '', '0', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', '2020-03-16 00:00:00', 1),
