(963, 121, 63, 'Due to increase of 30% in the price of a colour  TV the sale is reduced, by 40%. What will be percentage change in income ?', '', 'top', '10% increase', '10% decrease', '35% decrease', '22% decrease', 'D', 63, 'C', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>Let the original sale be Rs.100&#160;</div><div>When it is reduced by 40% the sale will be 60%&#160;</div><div>Increase in the price = 30%&#160;</div><div>The income will be 100+30 = 130%</div><div>$\\therefore$ The income for $60 \\%$ of sale $=\\frac{60}{100} \\times 130=78 \\%$<br></div><div><span>.\'.&#160;</span>The income will be decreased by (100%-78%) = 22%</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(964, 121, 64, 'Find the least number which when divided by 24,32 and 36 leaves the remainders 19, 27 and 31 respectively.', '', 'top', '280', '290', '283', '300', 'C', 64, 'B', '<b>(C)</b>&#160;<div><br></div><div>L.C.M. = 4x3x2x4x3 = 288&#160;</div><div>24 - 19=5&#160;</div><div>32 - 27=5&#160;</div><div>36 - 31=5&#160;</div><div>Hence, \'5\' should be subtracted from 288&#10;since it leaves the remainders.</div><div>&#160;.\'. The least number is (288 - 5) = 283</div>', 'uploads/fe5c77d455234a51ad72b7151949aa32.png', 'top', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(965, 121, 65, 'If LCM of \"a\" and \"b\" is a and LCM of \"b\" and \"c\" is b. then what is the LCM of \"c\" and \"a\".', '', 'top', 'a', 'b', 'c', 'abc', 'A', 65, 'D', '<b>(A)</b><div>L.C.M of \'a\' and \'b\' = a&#160;<div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;a x b = a&#160;</div><div>$$b=\\frac{a}{a}=1$$&#160;</div><div>L.C.M of \'b\' and \'c\' = b</div><div>&#160;$$C=\\frac{b}{b}=1$$</div><div>.\'. L.C.M. of \'c&#8217; and \'a\'  =  1 x a = a</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(966, 121, 66, 'Which one is correct ?', '', 'top', '$$\\frac{-3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{1}{2}$$<br>', '$$-\\frac{3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{1}{2}$$<br>', '$$-\\frac{3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{1}{2}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{1}{2}&lt;\\frac{-3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}$$<br>', 'A', 66, 'D', '$$\\text { A) } \\frac{-3}{5}&lt;\\frac{-13}{40}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{-1}{20}&lt;\\frac{1}{2}$$<br><div>$$=\\frac{-48&lt;-26-15&lt;-4&lt;40}{80}$$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{-48&lt;-26&lt;15&lt;-4&lt;40}{80}$$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{-48}{80}&lt;\\frac{-26}{80}&lt;\\frac{-15}{80}&lt;\\frac{-4}{80}&lt;\\frac{40}{80}$$<br></div><div>This is the correct order</div><div>&#160;Option (A) is correct.</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(967, 121, 67, '$$\\text { Simplify } \\cdot \\frac{x^{2}-25}{x+3} \\div \\frac{(x+5)^{2}}{x^{2}-9}$$<br>', '', 'top', '$$\\frac{(x-5)(x+3)}{(x-3)}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{(x-5)(x-3)}{(x+5)}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{(x+5)(x-3)}{(x+3)}$$<br>', '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$\\frac{(x+5)(x+3)}{(x-5)}$$</font><br>', 'B', 67, 'D', '(B)\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\frac{x^{2}-25}{x+3} \\div \\frac{(x+5)^{2}}{x^{2}-9} \\\\\n=& \\frac{(x+5)(x-5)}{(x+3)} \\times \\frac{(x+3)(x-3)}{(x+5)(x+5)} \\\\\n=& \\frac{(x-5)(x-3)}{(x+5)}\n\\end{aligned}$$', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
