(1091, 126, 77, 'A fair die is rolled. Find the probability of getting a prime factor of 6', '', 'top', '<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$\\frac{2}{3}$$</font><br>', '$$\\frac{1}{3}$$', '$$\\frac{5}{6}$$', '$$\\frac{1}{2}$$', 'B', 77, 'C', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>The faces of a die = 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6&#160;</div><div>Prime factors of 6 are= {2, 3}</div><div>.\'.  n(S) = 6, n(E) = 2&#160;</div><div>&#160;.\'. Probability of getting a prime factor of 6,&#10;&#10;$$P(E)=\\frac{n(E)}{n(S)}=\\frac{2}{6}=\\frac{1}{3}$$</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1092, 126, 154, 'Pocket money received by 7 students is given&#10;below.&#160;<div>&#8377; 42,&#160;&#8377; 22,&#160;&#8377; 40,&#160;&#8377; 26, &#8377; 23, &#8377; 28, &#8377; 43&#160;</div><div>Find the median.</div>', '', 'top', '&#8377;26', '&#8377;23', '&#8377;28', '&#8377;22', 'C', 154, 'C', '<b>(C)</b><div>Pocket money of 7 students = 42, 22, 40, 26, 23, 28, 43&#160;</div><div>Arranging them in ascending order = 22, 23, 26, 28, 40, 42, 43&#160;</div><div>Median of odd number of items&#10;&#10;$$=\\frac{n+1}{2}=\\frac{7+1}{2}=4^{\\text {th }} \\text { item (i.e) } 28$$&#160;</div><div>.\'. 4th number (ie) = 28 is the median</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
