(1178, 129, 157, 'The average height of 10 students in a class&#10;was calculated as 150 cm. On verification it&#10;was found that one reading was wrongly&#10;recorded as 130 cm instead of 140 cm. Find&#10;the correct mean height.', '', 'top', '150 cm', '152 cm', '153 cm', '151 cm', 'D', 157, 'C', '<b>(D)&#160;</b><div>The average height of 10 students = 150 cm&#160;</div><div>&#160; &#160;.\'. Total height&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;= 150 x 10&#160;<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">&#160;</font>= 1500 cm&#160;</div><div>Difference in the readings = 140 - 130 = 10</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ---------------</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;Total&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;=&#160; 1510</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ---------------</div><div>$$\\therefore \\text { The correct mean height }=\\frac{1510}{10}=151 \\mathrm{cm}$$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1179, 129, 158, 'What is the Mean of all two digit Numbers ?', '', 'top', '54.5', '49.5', '45.5', '44.5', 'A', 158, 'D', '<b>(A)</b>&#160;<div>Two digit numbers are from 10 to 99 = 90 Nos.&#160;</div><div>Sum of the numbers = 10 + 11 + 12 + 13 + &#8230;&#8230;. + 99&#160;</div><div>n = 90&#160;</div><div>$$S_{n}=\\frac{n}{2} \\times(a+l)$$<br></div><div>$$S_{90}=\\frac{90}{2} \\times(10+99)$$<br></div><div>$$=45 \\times 109=4905$$<br></div><div>$\\therefore$ Mean of the numbers $=\\frac{4905}{90}=54.5$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1180, 129, 159, 'If<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">&#160;</font>ax<sup>2</sup>-28x+49=0 has equal roots. Then the&#10;value of a is', '', 'top', '1', '2', '3', '4', 'D', 159, 'D', '<b>(D)&#160;</b><br><div><span>ax</span><sup>2</sup><span>-28x+49=0 has equal roots&#160;</span></div><div><span>Let the roots be&#160;</span><span>&#945;</span><span>&#160;and&#160;</span><span>&#945;</span></div><div><span>.\'. Sum of the roots<br></span></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$(\\alpha+\\alpha) \\quad=\\frac{-b}{a}=\\frac{-(-28)}{a}=\\frac{28}{a}$$</font><br></div><div><span>$$\\alpha+\\alpha=\\frac{28}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$2 \\alpha \\quad=\\frac{28}{a}[\\because \\text { roots are equal }]$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\alpha=\\frac{28}{2 a}=\\frac{14}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\text { The product of the roots }=\\alpha \\times \\alpha=\\alpha^{2}=\\frac{c}{a}=\\frac{49}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\alpha^{2}=\\frac{49}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\frac{14}{a} \\times \\frac{14}{a}=\\frac{49}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\frac{196}{a}=49$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$a=\\frac{196}{49}=4$$<br></span></div><div><span>.\'. The value of \'a\' = 4<br></span></div><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b></b></p>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
