(1216, 131, 58, 'A ramp for unloading a moving truck has an angle of elevation of 30<span>&#730;</span>. If the top of the ramp is 0.9 m above the ground level then find the length of the ramp.', '', 'top', '2 m', '1.5 m', '1.8 m', '1.6 m', 'C', 58, 'A', '<b>(C)&#160;</b><div>&#160;In the figure, Ac is the ramp.&#160;</div><div>Let the length of the ramp be \'l \' m&#160;</div><div>$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\sin 30=\\frac{0.9}{1}\\\\&#10;&amp;\\frac{1}{2}=\\frac{0.9}{1}&#10;\\end{aligned}$$&#160;&#160;</div><div><span>l=0.9 x 2m = 1.8m</span></div><div>&#160;.\'. The length of the ramp = 1.8 m</div>', 'uploads/da593f1e3fb9c019d2d43fa18a64a9e8.jpg', 'top', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1217, 131, 59, 'The standard deviation of 10 values is 3. If each value is increased by 4 find the variance of the new set of value.', '', 'top', '30', '12', '9', '$$\\sqrt{3}$$', 'C', 59, 'B', '<b>(C)</b>&#160;<div>If each value of a set is increased by some number evenly, &#10;there will be no increase in the standard deviation and the variance.&#160;<div>&#10;Hence the standard deviation of the 10 values will be the same.&#160;</div><div>$\\therefore$ The variance of the new set of value $=3^{2}=9$</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1218, 131, 57, 'A man travelled 2/11 of his journey by coach,17/22 by rail and walked the remaining 1 km. How far did he go ?', '', 'top', '22 km', '20 km', '33 km', '27 km', 'A', 57, 'B', '<b>(A)</b>&#160;<div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">Let the distance covered by him be x km.</font></div><div><div>$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\therefore x-\\left(\\frac{2}{11} x+\\frac{17}{22} x\\right)=1 \\mathrm{km}\\\\&#10;&amp;x-\\left(\\frac{4 x+17 x}{22}\\right)=1 \\mathrm{km}\\\\&#10;&amp;x-\\frac{21}{22} x=1 \\mathrm{km}&#10;\\end{aligned}$$&#10;$$\\frac{22 x-21 x}{22}=1 \\mathrm{km}$$&#10;$$x=1 \\times 22=22 \\mathrm{km}$$&#10;&#8756; The distance he went = 22Km</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1219, 131, 62, 'Shyam\'s monthly income is Rs.12,000. He saves Rs.1200. Find the percent of his savings and his expenditure', '', 'top', '10%,80%', '10%, 90%', '80%, 10%', '90%\' 10%', 'B', 62, 'B', '<table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"324\">&#10; <tbody><tr>&#10;  <td width=\"210\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br></p></td><td width=\"114\" colspan=\"2\"></td></tr><tr><td width=\"210\" valign=\"top\"><table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"324\">&#10; <tbody><tr>&#10;  <td width=\"210\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>(B)</b></p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"114\" colspan=\"2\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;</p></td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"210\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">Shyam\'s monthly income</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"24\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">=</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"90\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">Rs. 12,000</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"210\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">Savings</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"24\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">=</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"90\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">Rs.&#160; &#160;&#160;1200</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"210\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Expenditure</p>&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;&#160;&#160; &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"24\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;</p>&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">=</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"90\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">--------------<br>&#10;  Rs. 10,800<br>&#10;  --------------</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10;</tbody></table></td><td width=\"24\" valign=\"top\"></td><td width=\"90\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10;</tbody></table><span>$\\%$ of his savings $=\\frac{1200}{12000} \\times 100=10 \\%$&#160;</span><div><span>$\\%$ of his expenditure $=\\frac{10800}{12000} \\times 100=90 \\%$&#160;</span></div><div>$\\therefore$ The percentages of savings &amp; expenditure&#10;$=10 \\%, 90 \\%$</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1220, 131, 57, 'A man travelled 2/11 of his journey by coach,17/22 by rail and walked the remaining 1 km. How far did he go ?', '', 'top', '22 km', '20 km', '33 km', '27 km', 'A', 57, 'B', '<b>(A)</b>&#160;<div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">Let the distance covered by him be x km.</font></div><div><div>$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\therefore x-\\left(\\frac{2}{11} x+\\frac{17}{22} x\\right)=1 \\mathrm{km}\\\\&#10;&amp;x-\\left(\\frac{4 x+17 x}{22}\\right)=1 \\mathrm{km}\\\\&#10;&amp;x-\\frac{21}{22} x=1 \\mathrm{km}&#10;\\end{aligned}$$&#10;$$\\frac{22 x-21 x}{22}=1 \\mathrm{km}$$&#10;$$x=1 \\times 22=22 \\mathrm{km}$$&#10;&#8756; The distance he went = 22Km</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1221, 131, 60, 'Find the next term of this sequence 11, 13, 17, 19, 23, .....', '', 'top', '25', '27', '29', '31', 'C', 60, 'B', '<b>(C)</b><br><div>11, 13, 77, 19, 23, .......&#160;</div><div>In this sequence all the terms are 2-digit prime numbers starting from 11.&#160;<div>Hence the next prime number in this sequence will be \'29\'.</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1222, 131, 63, 'Due to increase of 30% in the price of a colour  TV the sale is reduced, by 40%. What will be percentage change in income ?', '', 'top', '10% increase', '10% decrease', '35% decrease', '22% decrease', 'D', 63, 'B', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>Let the original sale be Rs.100&#160;</div><div>When it is reduced by 40% the sale will be 60%&#160;</div><div>Increase in the price = 30%&#160;</div><div>The income will be 100+30 = 130%</div><div>$\\therefore$ The income for $60 \\%$ of sale $=\\frac{60}{100} \\times 130=78 \\%$<br></div><div><span>.\'.&#160;</span>The income will be decreased by (100%-78%) = 22%</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1223, 131, 64, 'Find the least number which when divided by 24,32 and 36 leaves the remainders 19, 27 and 31 respectively.', '', 'top', '280', '290', '283', '300', 'C', 64, 'B', '<b>(C)</b>&#160;<div><br></div><div>L.C.M. = 4x3x2x4x3 = 288&#160;</div><div>24 - 19=5&#160;</div><div>32 - 27=5&#160;</div><div>36 - 31=5&#160;</div><div>Hence, \'5\' should be subtracted from 288&#10;since it leaves the remainders.</div><div>&#160;.\'. The least number is (288 - 5) = 283</div>', 'uploads/fe5c77d455234a51ad72b7151949aa32.png', 'top', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1224, 131, 65, 'If LCM of \"a\" and \"b\" is a and LCM of \"b\" and \"c\" is b. then what is the LCM of \"c\" and \"a\".', '', 'top', 'a', 'b', 'c', 'abc', 'A', 65, 'B', '<b>(A)</b><div>L.C.M of \'a\' and \'b\' = a&#160;<div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;a x b = a&#160;</div><div>$$b=\\frac{a}{a}=1$$&#160;</div><div>L.C.M of \'b\' and \'c\' = b</div><div>&#160;$$C=\\frac{b}{b}=1$$</div><div>.\'. L.C.M. of \'c&#8217; and \'a\'  =  1 x a = a</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1225, 131, 63, 'Due to increase of 30% in the price of a colour  TV the sale is reduced, by 40%. What will be percentage change in income ?', '', 'top', '10% increase', '10% decrease', '35% decrease', '22% decrease', 'D', 63, 'B', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>Let the original sale be Rs.100&#160;</div><div>When it is reduced by 40% the sale will be 60%&#160;</div><div>Increase in the price = 30%&#160;</div><div>The income will be 100+30 = 130%</div><div>$\\therefore$ The income for $60 \\%$ of sale $=\\frac{60}{100} \\times 130=78 \\%$<br></div><div><span>.\'.&#160;</span>The income will be decreased by (100%-78%) = 22%</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1226, 131, 68, '$$\\text { Simplify } \\frac{2}{7}-\\left\\{\\left(\\frac{1}{4} \\div \\frac{2}{3}\\right)-\\frac{5}{6}\\right\\}$$<br>', '', 'top', '$$\\frac{168}{125}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{125}{160}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{125}{168}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{160}{125}$$<br>', 'C', 68, 'B', '<div><b>(C)</b></div>$$\\frac{2}{7}-\\left\\{\\left(\\frac{1}{4} \\div \\frac{2}{3}\\right)-\\frac{5}{6}\\right\\}$$<div>$$=\\frac{2}{7}-\\left\\{\\left(\\frac{1}{4} \\times \\frac{3}{2}\\right)-\\frac{5}{6}\\right\\}=\\frac{2}{7}-\\left\\{\\left(\\frac{3}{8}\\right)-\\frac{5}{6}\\right\\}$$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{2}{7}-\\left(\\frac{9-20}{24}\\right)=\\frac{2}{7}-\\left(\\frac{-11}{24}\\right)=\\frac{48+77}{168}=\\frac{125}{168}$$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1227, 131, 69, 'The exterior angles of a pentagon are in the ratio 6:3:4:3:2. Find all its interior angles.', '', 'top', '60&#730;, 120&#730;, 80&#730;, 160&#730;, 120&#730;', '80&#730;, 110&#730;, 150&#730;, 120&#730;, 80&#730;', '100&#730;, 170&#730;, 160&#730;, 40&#730;, 70&#730;', '60&#730;, 120&#730;, 100&#730;, 120&#730;, 140&#730;', 'D', 69, 'B', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>The sum of the exterior angles of a pentagon = 360<span>&#730;</span>&#160;</div><div>The ratio of the exterior angles of the pentagon is = 6:3:4:3:2:2&#160;</div><div>&#160;Let them be 6x,3x, 4x,3x, &amp; 2x&#160;</div><div>&#160;.\'. The exterior angles are&#160;</div><div><div>i) $\\frac{6 x}{18 x} \\times 360=120^{\\circ}$</div><div>ii) $\\frac{3 x}{18 x} \\times 360=60^{\\circ}$</div><div>iii) $\\frac{4 x}{18 x} \\times 360=80^{\\circ}$</div><div>iv) $\\frac{3 x}{18 x} \\times 360=60^{\\circ}$</div><div>v) $\\frac{2 x}{18 x} \\times 360=40^{\\circ}$</div></div><div><div>The exterior angles are 120<span>&#730;, 60</span><span>&#730;, 80</span><span>&#730;, 60</span><span>&#730;, 40</span><span>&#730;</span></div><div>.\'. The interior angles are</div><div>= ( 180<span>&#730;</span><span>-120</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), ( 180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-60</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), ( 180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-80</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), ( 180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-60</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), (180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-40</span><span>&#730;</span><span>)</span></div><div>= 60<span>&#730;, 120</span><span>&#730;, 100</span><span>&#730;, 120</span><span>&#730;, 140</span><span>&#730;</span></div></div>', 'uploads/f7fbcfabc30928201fbccc287d510d3c.jpg', 'top', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
