(1250, 138, 63, 'Due to increase of 30% in the price of a colour  TV the sale is reduced, by 40%. What will be percentage change in income ?', '', 'top', '10% increase', '10% decrease', '35% decrease', '22% decrease', 'D', 63, 'B', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>Let the original sale be Rs.100&#160;</div><div>When it is reduced by 40% the sale will be 60%&#160;</div><div>Increase in the price = 30%&#160;</div><div>The income will be 100+30 = 130%</div><div>$\\therefore$ The income for $60 \\%$ of sale $=\\frac{60}{100} \\times 130=78 \\%$<br></div><div><span>.\'.&#160;</span>The income will be decreased by (100%-78%) = 22%</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
