(1296, 139, 154, 'Pocket money received by 7 students is given&#10;below.&#160;<div>&#8377; 42,&#160;&#8377; 22,&#160;&#8377; 40,&#160;&#8377; 26, &#8377; 23, &#8377; 28, &#8377; 43&#160;</div><div>Find the median.</div>', '', 'top', '&#8377;26', '&#8377;23', '&#8377;28', '&#8377;22', 'C', 154, 'A', '<b>(C)</b><div>Pocket money of 7 students = 42, 22, 40, 26, 23, 28, 43&#160;</div><div>Arranging them in ascending order = 22, 23, 26, 28, 40, 42, 43&#160;</div><div>Median of odd number of items&#10;&#10;$$=\\frac{n+1}{2}=\\frac{7+1}{2}=4^{\\text {th }} \\text { item (i.e) } 28$$&#160;</div><div>.\'. 4th number (ie) = 28 is the median</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
