(1298, 139, 156, 'The students of a class donated &#8377;4624 for Chief&#10;Minister\'s State Relief Fund. Each student donated&#10;as many rupees as the number of students in the&#10;class. Find the number of students in the class.', '', 'top', '64', '68', '62', '78', 'B', 156, 'A', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>Let the number of students in the class be = x&#160;</div><div>.\'. Amount donated by each student = Rs x&#160;</div><div><table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">&#10; <tbody><tr>&#10;  <td width=\"115\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">.\'. Total amount</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"156\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">= X X X</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"115\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"156\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">= 4624</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"115\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; x<sup>2</sup> </p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"156\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">= 4624</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"271\" colspan=\"3\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$x=\\sqrt{4624}=68$$</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"226\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">.\'. the number is =68</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br></p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; &#10; <tr height=\"0\">&#10;  <td width=\"115\"></td>&#10;  <td width=\"111\"></td>&#10;  <td width=\"45\"></td>&#10; </tr>&#10; &#10;</tbody></table></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1299, 139, 157, 'The average height of 10 students in a class&#10;was calculated as 150 cm. On verification it&#10;was found that one reading was wrongly&#10;recorded as 130 cm instead of 140 cm. Find&#10;the correct mean height.', '', 'top', '150 cm', '152 cm', '153 cm', '151 cm', 'D', 157, 'A', '<b>(D)&#160;</b><div>The average height of 10 students = 150 cm&#160;</div><div>&#160; &#160;.\'. Total height&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;= 150 x 10&#160;<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">&#160;</font>= 1500 cm&#160;</div><div>Difference in the readings = 140 - 130 = 10</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ---------------</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;Total&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;=&#160; 1510</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ---------------</div><div>$$\\therefore \\text { The correct mean height }=\\frac{1510}{10}=151 \\mathrm{cm}$$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1300, 139, 158, 'What is the Mean of all two digit Numbers ?', '', 'top', '54.5', '49.5', '45.5', '44.5', 'A', 158, 'B', '<b>(A)</b>&#160;<div>Two digit numbers are from 10 to 99 = 90 Nos.&#160;</div><div>Sum of the numbers = 10 + 11 + 12 + 13 + &#8230;&#8230;. + 99&#160;</div><div>n = 90&#160;</div><div>$$S_{n}=\\frac{n}{2} \\times(a+l)$$<br></div><div>$$S_{90}=\\frac{90}{2} \\times(10+99)$$<br></div><div>$$=45 \\times 109=4905$$<br></div><div>$\\therefore$ Mean of the numbers $=\\frac{4905}{90}=54.5$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1301, 139, 159, 'If<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">&#160;</font>ax<sup>2</sup>-28x+49=0 has equal roots. Then the&#10;value of a is', '', 'top', '1', '2', '3', '4', 'D', 159, 'A', '<b>(D)&#160;</b><br><div><span>ax</span><sup>2</sup><span>-28x+49=0 has equal roots&#160;</span></div><div><span>Let the roots be&#160;</span><span>&#945;</span><span>&#160;and&#160;</span><span>&#945;</span></div><div><span>.\'. Sum of the roots<br></span></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$(\\alpha+\\alpha) \\quad=\\frac{-b}{a}=\\frac{-(-28)}{a}=\\frac{28}{a}$$</font><br></div><div><span>$$\\alpha+\\alpha=\\frac{28}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$2 \\alpha \\quad=\\frac{28}{a}[\\because \\text { roots are equal }]$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\alpha=\\frac{28}{2 a}=\\frac{14}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\text { The product of the roots }=\\alpha \\times \\alpha=\\alpha^{2}=\\frac{c}{a}=\\frac{49}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\alpha^{2}=\\frac{49}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\frac{14}{a} \\times \\frac{14}{a}=\\frac{49}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\frac{196}{a}=49$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$a=\\frac{196}{49}=4$$<br></span></div><div><span>.\'. The value of \'a\' = 4<br></span></div><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b></b></p>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1302, 139, 160, 'Find the median of the data.&#10;12, 14, 25, 23, 18, 17, 24, 20', '', 'top', '23', '18', '17', '19', 'D', 160, 'D', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>12, 14, 25, 23, 18, 17, 24, 20&#10;&#160;</div><div>Arranging in ascending order = 12, 14, 17, <u>18</u>, <u>20</u>, 23, 24, 25&#160;</div><div>Median of even number of items&#160;</div><div>$$=\\frac{n^{t h}}{2},\\left(\\frac{n}{2}+1\\right)^{t h} \\text { items }$$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{8}{2}=4^{t h},\\left(\\frac{8}{2}+1\\right)=5^{t h}$$<br></div><div><div>Average of them</div><div>$$=\\frac{18+20}{2}=\\frac{38}{2}=19$$<br></div><div>$\\therefore$ The median $=19$</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1303, 139, 161, 'In a two digit number, the digit in the unit place\nis twice of the digit in the tenth place. If the\ndigits are reversed, the new number is 27 more\nthan the given number. Find the number.', '', 'top', '63', '36', '93', '39', 'B', 161, 'B', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span>(B)&#160;</span></b><span></span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Let the number be xy&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160; &#160; &#160; y &#160;= 2x&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>2x - y = 0 &#8230;&#8230;&#8230;.(1)&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>If the digits are reversed the new&#10;number = yx&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>10x + y + 27&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &#160;&#160;= 10y + x&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>10x - 10y + y - x &#160;= -27&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>9x - 9y &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;= -27&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>$$x-y=\\frac{-27}{9}= -3$$&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>x &#160;&#8211; y = -3 &#8230;&#8230;&#8230;. (2)&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>2x &#8211; y = 0 ............ (1)</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>-------------------</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>(sub) - x = -3</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; x = 3</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#10;x - y = -3</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#10;3 - y = -3</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; -y = -3-3 = -6</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; y = 6</sp