(1364, 141, 157, 'The average height of 10 students in a class&#10;was calculated as 150 cm. On verification it&#10;was found that one reading was wrongly&#10;recorded as 130 cm instead of 140 cm. Find&#10;the correct mean height.', '', 'top', '150 cm', '152 cm', '153 cm', '151 cm', 'D', 157, 'A', '<b>(D)&#160;</b><div>The average height of 10 students = 150 cm&#160;</div><div>&#160; &#160;.\'. Total height&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;= 150 x 10&#160;<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">&#160;</font>= 1500 cm&#160;</div><div>Difference in the readings = 140 - 130 = 10</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ---------------</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;Total&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;=&#160; 1510</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ---------------</div><div>$$\\therefore \\text { The correct mean height }=\\frac{1510}{10}=151 \\mathrm{cm}$$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1365, 141, 159, 'If<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">&#160;</font>ax<sup>2</sup>-28x+49=0 has equal roots. Then the&#10;value of a is', '', 'top', '1', '2', '3', '4', 'D', 159, 'C', '<b>(D)&#160;</b><br><div><span>ax</span><sup>2</sup><span>-28x+49=0 has equal roots&#160;</span></div><div><span>Let the roots be&#160;</span><span>&#945;</span><span>&#160;and&#160;</span><span>&#945;</span></div><div><span>.\'. Sum of the roots<br></span></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$(\\alpha+\\alpha) \\quad=\\frac{-b}{a}=\\frac{-(-28)}{a}=\\frac{28}{a}$$</font><br></div><div><span>$$\\alpha+\\alpha=\\frac{28}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$2 \\alpha \\quad=\\frac{28}{a}[\\because \\text { roots are equal }]$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\alpha=\\frac{28}{2 a}=\\frac{14}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\text { The product of the roots }=\\alpha \\times \\alpha=\\alpha^{2}=\\frac{c}{a}=\\frac{49}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\alpha^{2}=\\frac{49}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\frac{14}{a} \\times \\frac{14}{a}=\\frac{49}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\frac{196}{a}=49$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$a=\\frac{196}{49}=4$$<br></span></div><div><span>.\'. The value of \'a\' = 4<br></span></div><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b></b></p>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1366, 141, 160, 'Find the median of the data.&#10;12, 14, 25, 23, 18, 17, 24, 20', '', 'top', '23', '18', '17', '19', 'D', 160, 'C', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>12, 14, 25, 23, 18, 17, 24, 20&#10;&#160;</div><div>Arranging in ascending order = 12, 14, 17, <u>18</u>, <u>20</u>, 23, 24, 25&#160;</div><div>Median of even number of items&#160;</div><div>$$=\\frac{n^{t h}}{2},\\left(\\frac{n}{2}+1\\right)^{t h} \\text { items }$$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{8}{2}=4^{t h},\\left(\\frac{8}{2}+1\\right)=5^{t h}$$<br></div><div><div>Average of them</div><div>$$=\\frac{18+20}{2}=\\frac{38}{2}=19$$<br></div><div>$\\therefore$ The median $=19$</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1367, 141, 59, 'The standard deviation of 10 values is 3. If each value is increased by 4 find the variance of the new set of value.', '', 'top', '30', '12', '9', '$$\\sqrt{3}$$', 'C', 59, 'A', '<b>(C)</b>&#160;<div>If each value of a set is increased by some number evenly, &#10;there will be no increase in the standard deviation and the variance.&#160;<div>&#10;Hence the standard deviation of the 10 values will be the same.&#160;</div><div>$\\therefore$ The variance of the new set of value $=3^{2}=9$</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1368, 141, 161, 'In a two digit number, the digit in the unit place\nis twice of the digit in the tenth place. If the\ndigits are reversed, the new number is 27 more\nthan the given number. Find the number.', '', 'top', '63', '36', '93', '39', 'B', 161, 'A', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span>(B)&#160;</span></b><span></span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>Let the number be xy&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160; &#160; &#160; y &#160;= 2x&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>2x - y = 0 &#8230;&#8230;&#8230;.(1)&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>If the digits are reversed the new&#10;number = yx&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>10x + y + 27&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &#160;&#160;= 10y + x&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>10x - 10y + y - x &#160;= -27&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>9x - 9y &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;= -27&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>$$x-y=\\frac{-27}{9}= -3$$&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>x &#160;&#8211; y = -3 &#8230;&#8230;&#8230;. (2)&#160;</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>2x &#8211; y = 0 ............ (1)</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>-------------------</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>(sub) - x = -3</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; x = 3</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#10;x - y = -3</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#10;3 - y = -3</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; -y = -3-3 = -6</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; y = 6</span></p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>.\'.&#160;The number = 36</span></p>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1369, 141, 162, 'The population of a village is 32,000. 40%  of\nthem are men. 25% of them are women and\nthe rest are children. Find the number of men and children', '', 'top', '12200 men, 11800 children', '12800 men, 11200 children', '12220 men, 12200 children', '12200 men, 11200 children', 'B', 162, 'B', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>The population of the village = 32,000&#160;</div><div>The percentage of men           = 40%&#160;</div><div>The percentage of women      = 25%&#160;</div><div>.\'. The percentage of children = 100%&#160;</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; = (40+25)%&#10;                                    </div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; = 100% - 65%</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; = 35%</div><div><div>The number of men $\\quad=\\frac{40}{100} \\times 32000$</div><div>$=12800$</div><div>The number of children $=\\frac{35}{100} \\times 32000$</div><div>$=11200$</div></div><div>The number of men and children respectively&#160;are 12800 &amp; 11200.<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1370, 141, 163, 'Find the greatest number of four digits exactly\ndivisible by 15, 21 and27', '', 'top', '9999', '9450', '9845', '8505', 'B', 163, 'D', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>$$\\frac{3 | 15,21,27}{5,7,9}$$</div><div>L.C.M = 3 x 5 x 7 x 9 = 945&#160;</div><div>.\'. Of the four numbers, 9450 is the greatest number which is exactly divisible by 945 &#10;(i.e. by 15, 21, 27) without remainder.</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1371, 141, 164, 'The GCD and LCM of two polynomials are x+1&#10;and&#160;<span>X<sup>4</sup>-1</span>&#160;respectively. If one of the polynomials&#10;is&#160;<span>X<sup>2</sup>+1</span>, find other one.<sup>&#160;</sup><sup>&#160;</sup><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span></span></p>', '', 'top', '<sup><span>&#160;</span></sup><span>X<sup>3</sup>-1</span><br>', '(x+ 1) (<span>X</span><sup>2</sup><span>-1</span>)', '<span>x</span><sup>2</sup><span>+x-1</span><br>', '<span>x</span><sup>2</sup><span>-x+1</span><br>', 'B', 164, 'D', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;&#10;<div>The product of two polynomials = G.C.D. x L.C.M of the two polynomials</div><div>$$P_{1} \\times P_{2}=(x+1) \\times\\left(x^{4}-1\\right)$$<br></div><div>$$\\left(x^{2}+1\\right) \\times P_{2}=(x+1) \\times\\left(x^{2}+1\\right)(x+1)(x-1)$$<br></div><div>$$P_{2}=\\frac{(x+1) \\times\\left(x^{2}+1\\right)(x+1)(x-1)}{\\left(x^{2}+1\\right)}$$<br></div><div>$$=(x+1)\\left(x^{2}-1\\right)$$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1372, 141, 165, 'Find the Highest Common Factor&#160;<span>4p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>3</sup><span>r, 8p</span><sup>3</sup><span>q</span><sup>2</sup><span>r</span><sup>2&#10;</sup><span>, 16p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>4</sup><span>r</span><sup>3</sup>', '', 'top', '<span>4p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>4</sup><span>r</span><sup>3</sup><br>', '<span>4p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>2</sup><span>r</span><br>', '<span>16p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>2</sup><span>r</span><br>', '<span>16p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>4</sup><span>r</span><sup>3</sup><br>', 'B', 165, 'D', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>4p<sup>2</sup>q<sup>3</sup>r, 8p<sup>3</sup>q<sup>2</sup>r<sup>2&#160;</sup>, 16p<sup>2</sup>q<sup>4</sup>r<sup>3</sup><br></div><div>H.C.F. of $16, 8, 4 = 4$&#160;</div><div>H.C.F. of $\\mathrm{P}^{2}, \\quad \\mathrm{P}^{3}, \\mathrm{P}^{2}=\\mathrm{p}^{2}$</div><div>H.C.F. of $\\mathbf{q}^{3}, \\quad \\mathbf{q}^{2}, \\mathbf{q}^{4}=\\mathbf{q}^{2}$</div><div>$$\\text { H.C.F. of } r, r^{2}, r^{3}=r$$<br></div><div>$$\\therefore \\text { H.C.F. }=4 p^{2} q^{2} r$$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1373, 141, 166, 'Simplify the following: <font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$\\frac{x^{3}}{x-2}+\\frac{8}{2-x}$$</font><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span></span></p>', '', 'top', '<span>x</span><sup>2</sup><span>-2x+4</span><br>', '<span>x</span><sup>2</sup><span>+2x+4</span>', '<span>x</span><sup>2</sup><span>-2x-4</span><br>', '<span>x</span><sup>2</sup><span>+2x-4</span><br>', 'B', 166, 'B', '<b>(B)&#160;&#10;</b><div>$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\frac{x^{3}}{x-2}+\\frac{8}{2-x}=\\frac{x^{3}}{(x-2)}+\\frac{8}{-(x-2)}\\\\&#10;&amp;\\frac{x^{3}-8}{(x-2)}=\\frac{(x-2)\\left(x^{2}+2 x+4\\right)}{(x-2)}=x^{2}+2 x+4&#10;\\end{aligned}$$</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1374, 141, 167, 'Simplify: $$\\frac{m}{m+1}+\\frac{1}{m+1}+\\frac{1}{m^{2}-1}$$<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span></span></p>', '', 'top', '<span>m</span><sup>2</sup><br>', '$$\\frac{m^{2}-1}{m^{2}}$$<br>', '$$\\frac{1}{m^{2}}$$', '$$\\frac{m^{2}}{m^{2}-1}$$', 'D', 167, 'D', '(D)\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\frac{m}{m+1}+\\frac{1}{m+1}+\\frac{1}{m^{2}-1} \\\\\n=& \\frac{m}{m+1}+\\frac{1}{m+1}+\\frac{1}{(m+1)(m-1)} \\\\\n=& \\frac{m(m-1)+(m-1)+1}{(m+1)(m-1)}=\\frac{m^{2}-m+m-1+1}{(m+1)(m-1)} \\\\\n=& \\frac{m^{2}}{\\left(m^{2}-1\\right)}\n\\end{aligned}$$', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1375, 142, 54, 'In a right triangular ground, the sides adjacent to the right angle are 50 m and 80 m. Find the cost of cementing the ground at Rs.5/sq.m', '', 'top', '&#8377;20000', '&#8377;15000', '&#8377;10000', '&#8377;12500', 'C', 54, 'B', '<b>(C)</b>&#160;<div>In the right triangular ground ABC, AB becomes the height of the triangle&#160;</div><div>And BC becomes the base of the triangle.&#160;</div><div>Area of the triangle$$=\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\mathrm{AB} \\times \\mathrm{BC}=\\frac{1}{2} \\times 80 \\times 50=2000 \\mathrm{sq.m}$$&#160;</div><div>.\'. The cost of cementing ground @ Rs.5/sq.m.&#160;</div><div><span>&#160;2000 x 5 = Rs.10,000/-</span></div>', 'uploads/3c206566a40113c85e440734cd5b9f7e.jpg', 'top', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1);
