(1421, 143, 54, 'In a right triangular ground, the sides adjacent to the right angle are 50 m and 80 m. Find the cost of cementing the ground at Rs.5/sq.m', '', 'top', '&#8377;20000', '&#8377;15000', '&#8377;10000', '&#8377;12500', 'C', 54, 'B', '<b>(C)</b>&#160;<div>In the right triangular ground ABC, AB becomes the height of the triangle&#160;</div><div>And BC becomes the base of the triangle.&#160;</div><div>Area of the triangle$$=\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\mathrm{AB} \\times \\mathrm{BC}=\\frac{1}{2} \\times 80 \\times 50=2000 \\mathrm{sq.m}$$&#160;</div><div>.\'. The cost of cementing ground @ Rs.5/sq.m.&#160;</div><div><span>&#160;2000 x 5 = Rs.10,000/-</span></div>', 'uploads/3c206566a40113c85e440734cd5b9f7e.jpg', 'top', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1422, 143, 56, 'A person crosses 600 m long street in 5 minutes. What is his speed in km Per hour?&#160;', '', 'top', '3.6', '7.2', '8.4', '10', 'B', 56, 'A', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\text { The person\'s speed }=\\frac{600 \\mathrm{m} \\times 60 \\mathrm{min}}{5 \\mathrm{min} \\times 1000 \\mathrm{m}} \\mathrm{km}\\\\&#10;&amp;=\\frac{36000}{5000}=7.2 \\mathrm{km}&#10;\\end{aligned}$$</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1423, 143, 58, 'A ramp for unloading a moving truck has an angle of elevation of 30<span>&#730;</span>. If the top of the ramp is 0.9 m above the ground level then find the length of the ramp.', '', 'top', '2 m', '1.5 m', '1.8 m', '1.6 m', 'C', 58, 'B', '<b>(C)&#160;</b><div>&#160;In the figure, Ac is the ramp.&#160;</div><div>Let the length of the ramp be \'l \' m&#160;</div><div>$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\sin 30=\\frac{0.9}{1}\\\\&#10;&amp;\\frac{1}{2}=\\frac{0.9}{1}&#10;\\end{aligned}$$&#160;&#160;</div><div><span>l=0.9 x 2m = 1.8m</span></div><div>&#160;.\'. The length of the ramp = 1.8 m</div>', 'uploads/da593f1e3fb9c019d2d43fa18a64a9e8.jpg', 'top', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1424, 143, 60, 'Find the next term of this sequence 11, 13, 17, 19, 23, .....', '', 'top', '25', '27', '29', '31', 'C', 60, 'A', '<b>(C)</b><br><div>11, 13, 77, 19, 23, .......&#160;</div><div>In this sequence all the terms are 2-digit prime numbers starting from 11.&#160;<div>Hence the next prime number in this sequence will be \'29\'.</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1425, 143, 63, 'Due to increase of 30% in the price of a colour  TV the sale is reduced, by 40%. What will be percentage change in income ?', '', 'top', '10% increase', '10% decrease', '35% decrease', '22% decrease', 'D', 63, 'B', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>Let the original sale be Rs.100&#160;</div><div>When it is reduced by 40% the sale will be 60%&#160;</div><div>Increase in the price = 30%&#160;</div><div>The income will be 100+30 = 130%</div><div>$\\therefore$ The income for $60 \\%$ of sale $=\\frac{60}{100} \\times 130=78 \\%$<br></div><div><span>.\'.&#160;</span>The income will be decreased by (100%-78%) = 22%</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
