(1455, 143, 168, 'If 3a+4b=22, 8a-5b=-4, then the value of&#160;<span>(a+b)</span><sup>2</sup>&#160;= ?', '', 'top', '36', '72', '25', '49', 'A', 168, 'B', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>(A)</b><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><br></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;3a + 4b = 22&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;..(1)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;8a - 5b&#160; = -4&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#8230;&#8230;&#8230;..(2)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ------------------------</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">(1)x5&#160; &#160; &#160; 15a + 20b = 110</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">(2)x4&#160; &#160; &#160; 32a -&#160; 20b&#160; = -16</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; -------------------------</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">(Add)&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; 47a = 94</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$a&#10;\\quad=\\frac{94}{47}=2$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">(subsititute a=2)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">3a + 4b = 22&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ..........(1)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">(3 x 2) + 4b = 22</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; 4b = 22 - 6 = 16</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$b=\\frac{16}{4}=4$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">.\'. (a+b)<sup>2</sup>&#10;= (2+4)<sup>2</sup> = 6<sup>2</sup> = 36</p>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1456, 143, 169, 'lhave a box which has 3 green, 9 blue, 4 yellow,&#10;8 orange coloured cubes in it.&#160;<div>a) What is the ratio of orange to yellow cubes?&#160;</div><div>b) What is the ratio of green to blue cubes?&#160;</div><div>c) How many different ratios can be formed,&#10;when you compare each colour to any one&#10;of the other colours ?</div>', '', 'top', '3:1   1:2   10 ratios', '1:3   2:1   4 ratios', '1:2   3:1   12 ratios', '2:1   1:3   12 ratios', 'D', 169, 'B', '<b>(D)&#160;</b><div>a)&#9;The ratio of orange to yellow cubes = 8 : 4&#160;</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; = 2 : 1&#160;</div><div>b)&#9;The ratio of green to blue cubes&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;= 3 : 9&#160;</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; = 1 : 3</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; = 4</div><div>c) No.&#160;<span>of coloured cubes&#160;</span><span>When anyone colour is&#160;</span><span>compared&#160;to any&#160;</span><span>other three colours the different ratios =&#160;</span><span>4 x 3 = 12 ratios</span></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1457, 143, 170, 'A troop has provisions fot 276 soldiers for 20\ndays. How many soldiers leave the troop so\nthat the provisions may last for 46 days.', '', 'top', '136', '156', '146', '164', 'B', 170, 'C', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>Days &#8211; Soldiers&#160;</div><div>&#160;20&#160; &#160; &#8211;&#160; 276&#160;</div><div>&#160;46&#160; &#160;&#160;<span>&#8211;</span><span>&#160; &#160;?&#160;</span></div><div>$$\\frac{20}{46} \\times 276=120$$&#160;</div><div>No. of soldiers who should leave the troop = 276 &#8211; 120 = 156</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1458, 143, 171, 'Using clay, a student made a right circular cone\nof height 48 cm and base radius 12 cm. Another\nstudent reshapes it in the form of sphere. Find\nthe radius of thd sphere.', '', 'top', '12 cm', '15 cm', '9 cm', '14 cm', 'A', 171, 'D', '<b>(A)</b>&#160;<div>Volume of the cone $=\\frac{1}{3} \\pi r^{2} h$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{1}{3} \\times \\pi \\times 12 \\times 12 \\times 48$$<br></div><div>Volume of the sphere = Volume of the cone</div><div>$$\\frac{4}{3} \\times \\pi r^{3} \\quad=\\frac{1}{3} \\times \\pi \\times 12 \\times 12 \\times 48$$<br></div><div>$$r^{3}=\\frac{1}{3} \\times \\frac{12 \\times 12 \\times 48 \\times 3}{4}$$<br></div><div><p class=\"MsoNormal\">r<sup>3&#160; </sup><span>= 1</span><span>2 x 12 x 12</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>r = 12</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span>.\'. The radius of the sphere = 12 cm</span></p></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1459, 143, 172, 'The radius of a spherical baloon increases from\n3 cm to 9 cm as air is being pumped into it.\nFind the ratio of volumes of the balloon in the\ntwo cases.', '', 'top', '1 : 3', '1 : 9', '1<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"> </font>: 27', '1<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"> </font>: 8', 'C', 172, 'A', '<b>(C)</b>&#160;<div>The ratio of the radii of the spherical balloon before &amp; after the air is pumped = 3 : 9 = 1 : 3&#160;</div><div><div>$\\therefore$ The ratio of their volumes</div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$=\\frac{4}{3} \\times \\pi \\times r_{1}^{3}: \\frac{4}{3} \\times \\pi \\times r_{2}^{3}$$</font><br></div></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$=1^{3}: 3^{3}=1: 27$$<br></font></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1460, 152, 54, 'In a right triangular ground, the sides adjacent to the right angle are 50 m and 80 m. Find the cost of cementing the ground at Rs.5/sq.m', '', 'top', '&#8377;20000', '&#8377;15000', '&#8377;10000', '&#8377;12500', 'C', 54, 'A', '<b>(C)</b>&#160;<div>In the right triangular ground ABC, AB becomes the height of the triangle&#160;</div><div>And BC becomes the base of the triangle.&#160;</div><div>Area of the triangle$$=\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\mathrm{AB} \\times \\mathrm{BC}=\\frac{1}{2} \\times 80 \\times 50=2000 \\mathrm{sq.m}$$&#160;</div><div>.\'. The cost of cementing ground @ Rs.5/sq.m.&#160;</div><div><span>&#160;2000 x 5 = Rs.10,000/-</span></div>', 'uploads/3c206566a40113c85e440734cd5b9f7e.jpg', 'top', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
