(1640, 160, 69, 'The exterior angles of a pentagon are in the ratio 6:3:4:3:2. Find all its interior angles.', '', 'top', '60&#730;, 120&#730;, 80&#730;, 160&#730;, 120&#730;', '80&#730;, 110&#730;, 150&#730;, 120&#730;, 80&#730;', '100&#730;, 170&#730;, 160&#730;, 40&#730;, 70&#730;', '60&#730;, 120&#730;, 100&#730;, 120&#730;, 140&#730;', 'D', 69, 'D', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>The sum of the exterior angles of a pentagon = 360<span>&#730;</span>&#160;</div><div>The ratio of the exterior angles of the pentagon is = 6:3:4:3:2:2&#160;</div><div>&#160;Let them be 6x,3x, 4x,3x, &amp; 2x&#160;</div><div>&#160;.\'. The exterior angles are&#160;</div><div><div>i) $\\frac{6 x}{18 x} \\times 360=120^{\\circ}$</div><div>ii) $\\frac{3 x}{18 x} \\times 360=60^{\\circ}$</div><div>iii) $\\frac{4 x}{18 x} \\times 360=80^{\\circ}$</div><div>iv) $\\frac{3 x}{18 x} \\times 360=60^{\\circ}$</div><div>v) $\\frac{2 x}{18 x} \\times 360=40^{\\circ}$</div></div><div><div>The exterior angles are 120<span>&#730;, 60</span><span>&#730;, 80</span><span>&#730;, 60</span><span>&#730;, 40</span><span>&#730;</span></div><div>.\'. The interior angles are</div><div>= ( 180<span>&#730;</span><span>-120</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), ( 180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-60</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), ( 180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-80</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), ( 180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-60</span><span>&#730;</span><span>), (180</span><span>&#730;</span><span>-40</span><span>&#730;</span><span>)</span></div><div>= 60<span>&#730;, 120</span><span>&#730;, 100</span><span>&#730;, 120</span><span>&#730;, 140</span><span>&#730;</span></div></div>', 'uploads/f7fbcfabc30928201fbccc287d510d3c.jpg', 'top', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
