(1652, 160, 156, 'The students of a class donated &#8377;4624 for Chief&#10;Minister\'s State Relief Fund. Each student donated&#10;as many rupees as the number of students in the&#10;class. Find the number of students in the class.', '', 'top', '64', '68', '62', '78', 'B', 156, 'A', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>Let the number of students in the class be = x&#160;</div><div>.\'. Amount donated by each student = Rs x&#160;</div><div><table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">&#10; <tbody><tr>&#10;  <td width=\"115\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">.\'. Total amount</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"156\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">= X X X</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"115\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"156\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">= 4624</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"115\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; x<sup>2</sup> </p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"156\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">= 4624</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"271\" colspan=\"3\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$x=\\sqrt{4624}=68$$</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"226\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">.\'. the number is =68</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br></p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; &#10; <tr height=\"0\">&#10;  <td width=\"115\"></td>&#10;  <td width=\"111\"></td>&#10;  <td width=\"45\"></td>&#10; </tr>&#10; &#10;</tbody></table></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1653, 160, 157, 'The average height of 10 students in a class&#10;was calculated as 150 cm. On verification it&#10;was found that one reading was wrongly&#10;recorded as 130 cm instead of 140 cm. Find&#10;the correct mean height.', '', 'top', '150 cm', '152 cm', '153 cm', '151 cm', 'D', 157, 'A', '<b>(D)&#160;</b><div>The average height of 10 students = 150 cm&#160;</div><div>&#160; &#160;.\'. Total height&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;= 150 x 10&#160;<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">&#160;</font>= 1500 cm&#160;</div><div>Difference in the readings = 140 - 130 = 10</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ---------------</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;Total&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;=&#160; 1510</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ---------------</div><div>$$\\therefore \\text { The correct mean height }=\\frac{1510}{10}=151 \\mathrm{cm}$$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1654, 160, 158, 'What is the Mean of all two digit Numbers ?', '', 'top', '54.5', '49.5', '45.5', '44.5', 'A', 158, 'C', '<b>(A)</b>&#160;<div>Two digit numbers are from 10 to 99 = 90 Nos.&#160;</div><div>Sum of the numbers = 10 + 11 + 12 + 13 + &#8230;&#8230;. + 99&#160;</div><div>n = 90&#160;</div><div>$$S_{n}=\\frac{n}{2} \\times(a+l)$$<br></div><div>$$S_{90}=\\frac{90}{2} \\times(10+99)$$<br></div><div>$$=45 \\times 109=4905$$<br></div><div>$\\therefore$ Mean of the numbers $=\\frac{4905}{90}=54.5$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1655, 160, 159, 'If<font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">&#160;</font>ax<sup>2</sup>-28x+49=0 has equal roots. Then the&#10;value of a is', '', 'top', '1', '2', '3', '4', 'D', 159, 'C', '<b>(D)&#160;</b><br><div><span>ax</span><sup>2</sup><span>-28x+49=0 has equal roots&#160;</span></div><div><span>Let the roots be&#160;</span><span>&#945;</span><span>&#160;and&#160;</span><span>&#945;</span></div><div><span>.\'. Sum of the roots<br></span></div><div><font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$(\\alpha+\\alpha) \\quad=\\frac{-b}{a}=\\frac{-(-28)}{a}=\\frac{28}{a}$$</font><br></div><div><span>$$\\alpha+\\alpha=\\frac{28}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$2 \\alpha \\quad=\\frac{28}{a}[\\because \\text { roots are equal }]$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\alpha=\\frac{28}{2 a}=\\frac{14}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\text { The product of the roots }=\\alpha \\times \\alpha=\\alpha^{2}=\\frac{c}{a}=\\frac{49}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\alpha^{2}=\\frac{49}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\frac{14}{a} \\times \\frac{14}{a}=\\frac{49}{a}$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$\\frac{196}{a}=49$$<br></span></div><div><span>$$a=\\frac{196}{49}=4$$<br></span></div><div><span>.\'. The value of \'a\' = 4<br></span></div><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b></b></p>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1656, 160, 160, 'Find the median of the data.&#10;12, 14, 25, 23, 18, 17, 24, 20', '', 'top', '23', '18', '17', '19', 'D', 160, 'C', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>12, 14, 25, 23, 18, 17, 24, 20&#10;&#160;</div><div>Arranging in ascending order = 12, 14, 17, <u>18</u>, <u>20</u>, 23, 24, 25&#160;</div><div>Median of even number of items&#160;</div><div>$$=\\frac{n^{t h}}{2},\\left(\\frac{n}{2}+1\\right)^{t h} \\text { items }$$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{8}{2}=4^{t h},\\left(\\frac{8}{2}+1\\right)=5^{t h}$$<br></div><div><div>Average of them</div><div>$$=\\frac{18+20}{2}=\\frac{38}{2}=19$$<br></div><div>$\\therefore$ The median $=19$</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1);
INSERT INTO `student_log_detail` (`student_log_detail_id`, `student_log_id`, `question_id`, `name`, `image_path`, `direction`, `a`, `b`, `c`, `d`, `answer`, `question_no`, `student_answer`, `explanation`, `image_path_explanation`, `explanation_img_direction`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `difficult_id`) VALUES
(1657, 160, 160, 'Find the median of the data.&#10;12, 14, 25, 23, 18, 17, 24, 20', '', 'top', '23', '18', '17', '19', 'D', 160, 'C', '<b>(D)</b>&#160;<div>12, 14, 25, 23, 18, 17, 24, 20&#10;&#160;</div><div>Arranging in ascending order = 12, 14, 17, <u>18</u>, <u>20</u>, 23, 24, 25&#160;</div><div>Median of even number of items&#160;</div><div>$$=\\frac{n^{t h}}{2},\\left(\\frac{n}{2}+1\\right)^{t h} \\text { items }$$<br></div><div>$$=\\frac{8}{2}=4^{t h},\\left(\\frac{8}{2}+1\\right)=5^{t h}$$<br></div><div><div>Average of them</div><div>$$=\\frac{18+20}{2}=\\frac{38}{2}=19$$<br></div><div>$\\therefore$ The median $=19$</div></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1658, 160, 162, 'The population of a village is 32,000. 40%  of\nthem are men. 25% of them are women and\nthe rest are children. Find the number of men and children', '', 'top', '12200 men, 11800 children', '12800 men, 11200 children', '12220 men, 12200 children', '12200 men, 11200 children', 'B', 162, 'B', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>The population of the village = 32,000&#160;</div><div>The percentage of men           = 40%&#160;</div><div>The percentage of women      = 25%&#160;</div><div>.\'. The percentage of children = 100%&#160;</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; = (40+25)%&#10;                                    </div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; = 100% - 65%</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; = 35%</div><div><div>The number of men $\\quad=\\frac{40}{100} \\times 32000$</div><div>$=12800$</div><div>The number of children $=\\frac{35}{100} \\times 32000$</div><div>$=11200$</div></div><div>The number of men and children respectively&#160;are 12800 &amp; 11200.<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1659, 160, 163, 'Find the greatest number of four digits exactly\ndivisible by 15, 21 and27', '', 'top', '9999', '9450', '9845', '8505', 'B', 163, 'C', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>$$\\frac{3 | 15,21,27}{5,7,9}$$</div><div>L.C.M = 3 x 5 x 7 x 9 = 945&#160;</div><div>.\'. Of the four numbers, 9450 is the greatest number which is exactly divisible by 945 &#10;(i.e. by 15, 21, 27) without remainder.</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1660, 160, 164, 'The GCD and LCM of two polynomials are x+1&#10;and&#160;<span>X<sup>4</sup>-1</span>&#160;respectively. If one of the polynomials&#10;is&#160;<span>X<sup>2</sup>+1</span>, find other one.<sup>&#160;</sup><sup>&#160;</sup><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span></span></p>', '', 'top', '<sup><span>&#160;</span></sup><span>X<sup>3</sup>-1</span><br>', '(x+ 1) (<span>X</span><sup>2</sup><span>-1</span>)', '<span>x</span><sup>2</sup><span>+x-1</span><br>', '<span>x</span><sup>2</sup><span>-x+1</span><br>', 'B', 164, 'C', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;&#10;<div>The product of two polynomials = G.C.D. x L.C.M of the two polynomials</div><div>$$P_{1} \\times P_{2}=(x+1) \\times\\left(x^{4}-1\\right)$$<br></div><div>$$\\left(x^{2}+1\\right) \\times P_{2}=(x+1) \\times\\left(x^{2}+1\\right)(x+1)(x-1)$$<br></div><div>$$P_{2}=\\frac{(x+1) \\times\\left(x^{2}+1\\right)(x+1)(x-1)}{\\left(x^{2}+1\\right)}$$<br></div><div>$$=(x+1)\\left(x^{2}-1\\right)$$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1661, 160, 165, 'Find the Highest Common Factor&#160;<span>4p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>3</sup><span>r, 8p</span><sup>3</sup><span>q</span><sup>2</sup><span>r</span><sup>2&#10;</sup><span>, 16p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>4</sup><span>r</span><sup>3</sup>', '', 'top', '<span>4p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>4</sup><span>r</span><sup>3</sup><br>', '<span>4p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>2</sup><span>r</span><br>', '<span>16p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>2</sup><span>r</span><br>', '<span>16p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>4</sup><span>r</span><sup>3</sup><br>', 'B', 165, 'D', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>4p<sup>2</sup>q<sup>3</sup>r, 8p<sup>3</sup>q<sup>2</sup>r<sup>2&#160;</sup>, 16p<sup>2</sup>q<sup>4</sup>r<sup>3</sup><br></div><div>H.C.F. of $16, 8, 4 = 4$&#160;</div><div>H.C.F. of $\\mathrm{P}^{2}, \\quad \\mathrm{P}^{3}, \\mathrm{P}^{2}=\\mathrm{p}^{2}$</div><div>H.C.F. of $\\mathbf{q}^{3}, \\quad \\mathbf{q}^{2}, \\mathbf{q}^{4}=\\mathbf{q}^{2}$</div><div>$$\\text { H.C.F. of } r, r^{2}, r^{3}=r$$<br></div><div>$$\\therefore \\text { H.C.F. }=4 p^{2} q^{2} r$$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1662, 160, 165, 'Find the Highest Common Factor&#160;<span>4p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>3</sup><span>r, 8p</span><sup>3</sup><span>q</span><sup>2</sup><span>r</span><sup>2&#10;</sup><span>, 16p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>4</sup><span>r</span><sup>3</sup>', '', 'top', '<span>4p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>4</sup><span>r</span><sup>3</sup><br>', '<span>4p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>2</sup><span>r</span><br>', '<span>16p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>2</sup><span>r</span><br>', '<span>16p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>4</sup><span>r</span><sup>3</sup><br>', 'B', 165, 'D', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>4p<sup>2</sup>q<sup>3</sup>r, 8p<sup>3</sup>q<sup>2</sup>r<sup>2&#160;</sup>, 16p<sup>2</sup>q<sup>4</sup>r<sup>3</sup><br></div><div>H.C.F. of $16, 8, 4 = 4$&#160;</div><div>H.C.F. of $\\mathrm{P}^{2}, \\quad \\mathrm{P}^{3}, \\mathrm{P}^{2}=\\mathrm{p}^{2}$</div><div>H.C.F. of $\\mathbf{q}^{3}, \\quad \\mathbf{q}^{2}, \\mathbf{q}^{4}=\\mathbf{q}^{2}$</div><div>$$\\text { H.C.F. of } r, r^{2}, r^{3}=r$$<br></div><div>$$\\therefore \\text { H.C.F. }=4 p^{2} q^{2} r$$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1663, 160, 168, 'If 3a+4b=22, 8a-5b=-4, then the value of&#160;<span>(a+b)</span><sup>2</sup>&#160;= ?', '', 'top', '36', '72', '25', '49', 'A', 168, 'D', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>(A)</b><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><br></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;3a + 4b = 22&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;&#8230;&#8230;&#8230;..(1)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;8a - 5b&#160; = -4&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#8230;&#8230;&#8230;..(2)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ------------------------</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">(1)x5&#160; &#160; &#160; 15a + 20b = 110</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">(2)x4&#160; &#160; &#160; 32a -&#160; 20b&#160; = -16</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; -------------------------</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">(Add)&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; 47a = 94</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$a&#10;\\quad=\\frac{94}{47}=2$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">(subsititute a=2)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">3a + 4b = 22&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; ..........(1)</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">(3 x 2) + 4b = 22</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; 4b = 22 - 6 = 16</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$b=\\frac{16}{4}=4$$</p>&#10;&#10;<p class=\"MsoNormal\">.\'. (a+b)<sup>2</sup>&#10;= (2+4)<sup>2</sup> = 6<sup>2</sup> = 36</p>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1664, 160, 169, 'lhave a box which has 3 green, 9 blue, 4 yellow,&#10;8 orange coloured cubes in it.&#160;<div>a) What is the ratio of orange to yellow cubes?&#160;</div><div>b) What is the ratio of green to blue cubes?&#160;</div><div>c) How many different ratios can be formed,&#10;when you compare each colour to any one&#10;of the other colours ?</div>', '', 'top', '3:1   1:2   10 ratios', '1:3   2:1   4 ratios', '1:2   3:1   12 ratios', '2:1   1:3   12 ratios', 'D', 169, 'A', '<b>(D)&#160;</b><div>a)&#9;The ratio of orange to yellow cubes = 8 : 4&#160;</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; = 2 : 1&#160;</div><div>b)&#9;The ratio of green to blue cubes&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;= 3 : 9&#160;</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; = 1 : 3</div><div>&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; = 4</div><div>c) No.&#160;<span>of coloured cubes&#160;</span><span>When anyone colour is&#160;</span><span>compared&#160;to any&#160;</span><span>other three colours the different ratios =&#160;</span><span>4 x 3 = 12 ratios</span></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1665, 160, 165, 'Find the Highest Common Factor&#160;<span>4p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>3</sup><span>r, 8p</span><sup>3</sup><span>q</span><sup>2</sup><span>r</span><sup>2&#10;</sup><span>, 16p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>4</sup><span>r</span><sup>3</sup>', '', 'top', '<span>4p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>4</sup><span>r</span><sup>3</sup><br>', '<span>4p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>2</sup><span>r</span><br>', '<span>16p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>2</sup><span>r</span><br>', '<span>16p</span><sup>2</sup><span>q</span><sup>4</sup><span>r</span><sup>3</sup><br>', 'B', 165, 'D', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>4p<sup>2</sup>q<sup>3</sup>r, 8p<sup>3</sup>q<sup>2</sup>r<sup>2&#160;</sup>, 16p<sup>2</sup>q<sup>4</sup>r<sup>3</sup><br></div><div>H.C.F. of $16, 8, 4 = 4$&#160;</div><div>H.C.F. of $\\mathrm{P}^{2}, \\quad \\mathrm{P}^{3}, \\mathrm{P}^{2}=\\mathrm{p}^{2}$</div><div>H.C.F. of $\\mathbf{q}^{3}, \\quad \\mathbf{q}^{2}, \\mathbf{q}^{4}=\\mathbf{q}^{2}$</div><div>$$\\text { H.C.F. of } r, r^{2}, r^{3}=r$$<br></div><div>$$\\therefore \\text { H.C.F. }=4 p^{2} q^{2} r$$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1666, 160, 166, 'Simplify the following: <font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\">$$\\frac{x^{3}}{x-2}+\\frac{8}{2-x}$$</font><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span></span></p>', '', 'top', '<span>x</span><sup>2</sup><span>-2x+4</span><br>', '<span>x</span><sup>2</sup><span>+2x+4</span>', '<span>x</span><sup>2</sup><span>-2x-4</span><br>', '<span>x</span><sup>2</sup><span>+2x-4</span><br>', 'B', 166, 'B', '<b>(B)&#160;&#10;</b><div>$$\\begin{aligned}&#10;&amp;\\frac{x^{3}}{x-2}+\\frac{8}{2-x}=\\frac{x^{3}}{(x-2)}+\\frac{8}{-(x-2)}\\\\&#10;&amp;\\frac{x^{3}-8}{(x-2)}=\\frac{(x-2)\\left(x^{2}+2 x+4\\right)}{(x-2)}=x^{2}+2 x+4&#10;\\end{aligned}$$</div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
