(1697, 161, 156, 'The students of a class donated &#8377;4624 for Chief&#10;Minister\'s State Relief Fund. Each student donated&#10;as many rupees as the number of students in the&#10;class. Find the number of students in the class.', '', 'top', '64', '68', '62', '78', 'B', 156, 'C', '<b>(B)</b>&#160;<div>Let the number of students in the class be = x&#160;</div><div>.\'. Amount donated by each student = Rs x&#160;</div><div><table class=\"MsoTableGrid\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">&#10; <tbody><tr>&#10;  <td width=\"115\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">.\'. Total amount</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"156\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">= X X X</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"115\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"156\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">= 4624</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"115\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; x<sup>2</sup> </p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"156\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">= 4624</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"271\" colspan=\"3\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">$$x=\\sqrt{4624}=68$$</p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; <tr>&#10;  <td width=\"226\" colspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\">.\'. the number is =68</p>&#10;  </td>&#10;  <td width=\"45\" valign=\"top\">&#10;  <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br></p>&#10;  </td>&#10; </tr>&#10; &#10; <tr height=\"0\">&#10;  <td width=\"115\"></td>&#10;  <td width=\"111\"></td>&#10;  <td width=\"45\"></td>&#10; </tr>&#10; &#10;</tbody></table></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
(1698, 161, 158, 'What is the Mean of all two digit Numbers ?', '', 'top', '54.5', '49.5', '45.5', '44.5', 'A', 158, 'C', '<b>(A)</b>&#160;<div>Two digit numbers are from 10 to 99 = 90 Nos.&#160;</div><div>Sum of the numbers = 10 + 11 + 12 + 13 + &#8230;&#8230;. + 99&#160;</div><div>n = 90&#160;</div><div>$$S_{n}=\\frac{n}{2} \\times(a+l)$$<br></div><div>$$S_{90}=\\frac{90}{2} \\times(10+99)$$<br></div><div>$$=45 \\times 109=4905$$<br></div><div>$\\therefore$ Mean of the numbers $=\\frac{4905}{90}=54.5$<br></div>', '', '0', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', '2020-03-17 00:00:00', 1),
